animal.description:
Sissy is a 1 yr old female pittie weighing about 50 lb. She is currently up to date on all vaccines and is scheduled to be spayed ASAP.  Overall Sissy is in good health with no concerns.

Behaviorally, Sissy is a friendly girl who enjoys everyone who comes offering attention and love.  Her past is a mystery, and while she has shown no concerning behavior whatsoever, she does take slightly longer to warm up to men. Once warming up, she loves them just the same. Sissy has shown to thrive in a pack & would do best living with another dog to help her remain confident and outgoing. She is just barely 1 year old & is polishing all her indoor manners and doing wonderfully.  She does great in the bath and loves rides in the car.  Overall Sissy is a great family dog in the making and she is patiently waiting for that family to find her!

Apply for Sissy directly at the link below!

https://pitofoursoulsrescue.com/our-dogs/adoption-application/

animal.description:
PLEASE READ: The clinics are not open for viewing animals. Since we currently can't meet you in person, if you are interested in meeting this pet, please email information about yourself, family, residence and current/prior pet experience. If it is a good fit you will be emailed an application. Once that is approved, arrangements will be made for a meeting. Thanks for your understanding!

Rosalind is an approximately 12 week old female Jack Russell (?) Mix who we believe should stay around the small side of the "medium" category. Unfortunately we don't know either parent so we can't say for sure what breed mix they are and ultimately what size they will be but this is our best guess. Rosalind and her littermates were rescued from a Kentucky shelter when their time was up. Her adoption fee is $399 and includes her spay, vaccinations, microchip and routine labwork. Please email us to start the adoption process.

For puppies 6 months and younger you must live within 50 miles of Oswego, IL.

Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes: 
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*: 
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming 
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old) 
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt: 
If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

For my Petfinder.com friends, please contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information. My ID number is 336261

I am available for adoption; however due to my breed my adoption will have to be facilitated through a rescue organization. Please see the front desk staff or contact the Shelter for more information.

Meet Turbo! Now this is a face, everyone will LOVE! Not only is Turbo quite photogenic, he has a fantastic personality! Turbo is a happy boy, who is exuberant and always ready to go...no matter what that means. When meeting his canine shelter friends, Turbo, did well. He is currently working on learning spacial awareness, and making progress! This stud would appreciate an active owner, one willing to continue working with him, keeping him busy and engaged. If you simply cannot resist this mug...come and meet handsome, Turbo!

The following descriptions describe behaviors that were observed during testing and/or veterinary examination: Evaluated for temperament with 336510 (female), and 336498 (male). Did very well with both. Did not back down from other male who was displaying unwanted behavior, but was not reactive. He is a strong, high energy dog. He has a very nice personality, and he talks and howls for attention 1/19/2021

American Pit Bulls are a misunderstood breed; for this reason, we implore adopters to these beautiful dogs to be very vigilant in training and socialization. This breed is very energetic and will need daily exercise. Because of their strength and energy, apartment living may not be the best fit. This breed can be loving, loyal and very smart. 

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption.

animal.description:
Foster location:  Boise ID 
Breed:  Pomeranian
Age:  11 years 
Adoption Fee:  $150.00

Neutered, Vaccinated, Microchipped

Adoption Application:  http://fuzzypawzrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application-2/


Shredder is a puppy and a grandpa in one fluffy 11 year old cuddly body and his Fuzzy Pawz Rescue foster family can’t wait to find him the perfect home.

This little old man wakes up in the morning its full zoomies for a bit and then it’s time for his long mid-morning nap. Once he is asleep don’t bother him or you will get a warning growl or he will get up and bark at you; no one likes to have their nap disturbed!  He loves hanging out with his people and just relaxing on the couch – no kids under 15 though.

He likes gentle walks but isn’t the best on leash - if he decides he has had enough he whips around and chews through his collar/ harness to be free from the nonsense. He likes to wander so a secure back yard and sometimes even a travel crate in the car is a must to avoid chasing him around the neighborhood.   He is an old man with a mind of his own and wants things on his terms.

He is not the biggest fan of the crate his foster family has tried getting him to call home while they are at the store and he likes to defend the house from deliveries and trash trucks so apartment living might be overwhelming for him. Shredder knows to warn you to let him outside but sometimes he gets so excited he pees where he is standing. He loves sunbathing and even sits outside protecting his backyard with a jacket on in the snow. 

Shredder tolerates other dogs but doesn’t want to play with them. If they get too much in his face he will warning snap at then. He has trained his foster brother huskies to abandon the chair if it is where he wants to be sleeping. He likely will do fine with a cat that just leaves him alone.

Shredder recently got his teeth cleaned and they are in good shape, he has some alopecia but tolerates grooming well, and he is neutered, microchipped, and up to date on his vaccinations. He will make a great addition to a calm environment who doesn’t mind a little Pomeranian sass every once and a while.

Available for Adoption: 2/6/2021 (Currently accepting applications).
Applications need to be approved before a meet and greet will be set up for any Fetching Hearts Rescue dogs. 

Meet Whiskey!!! He came into the shelter with another brother and two sisters.  He is looking for his forever family now to enjoy life with.  He is looking for a family to play with him, teach/train him and take him on explorations with them.  Whiskey is a sweet boy who just loves life and loves to play, eat and sleep.  Being that he is a young pup, he will need a family who will give him plenty of attention, time and training.  Puppies are take a lot of time, so we want to make sure that families are ready for them.  He loves his doggie friends and would enjoy a fenced yard to run around in.  If you are ready for a puppy, please apply today!!

If interested in Whiskey, please email to inquire at: SCREENING.FETCHINGHEARTS@GMAIL.COM OR COPY LINK BELOW TO APPLY AND FILL OUT AN APPLICATION: https://www.fetchingheartsrescue.org/adoption-form-online
to fill out an application.

Unless otherwise indicated, all dogs adopted through Fetching Hearts have received the following before being available for adoption:

Thorough veterinary examination.

All routine annual vaccinations, including Rabies, DHLPP, Bordatella (Kennel Cough), Heartworm Test, Fecal Test, Deworming, Microchip, Flea and Tick Prevention and Heartworm Prevention.

Spay/Neuter.
All dogs are quarantined for two weeks outside of the shelter (puppies four weeks) to ensure they don't break with disease.

VETTING NOTE: Fetching Hearts Rescue completely vets our dogs thoroughly to the best of our knowledge based on communication with our Southern Vets. If anything is brought to our attention, we treat the dog. After adopting the dog, you will be responsible for following up with all vetting going forward.

HEARTWORM NOTE: Dogs who were treated for Heartworm can test positive up to 4-6 months after last treatment. All dogs are immediately put on Heartguard/Ivermectin following the treatment to kill the Heartworm larvae. All dogs should be re-tested after 5-6 months from the last Heartworm treatment.

animal.description:
Buddy is our beautiful 18 month old shepherd mix with the sweetest face & a happy tail. He weighs 80 pounds. 

This one is a lover. He has a lovely disposition. Happy & fun. 

He is neutered, micro-chipped and up to date on all immunizations. Buddy is a sweet, friendly guy. Well socialized, he loves everyone. Extremely smart. He could be trained for anything. Great with other dogs. 

Buddy lives in a home with numerous other pups and gets along well with all of them. He is playful, happy and loves to play with the other rescue dogs.

If you are interested in giving Buddy a wonderful home, go to our Facebook page and download the application from the "Notes" section. While you are there, please "Like" our page to see our available dogs and keep up with upcoming events.

Here is the link: www.facebook.com/pages/MAR-Mercer-Animal-Rescue-501c3/374149832631589

You can also email us at merceranimalrescue@gmail.com and we will email an application to you. 
It can also be downloaded from our website: www.merceranimalrescue.org

Buddy’s adoption donation is $525 which helps to cover his neutering, microchipping, shots, bordetella (kennel cough), rabies, flea/tick prevention, heart worm prevention, heart worm test, vet examination, certificate of health and cost of transport. 

Buddy had a heart worm test last week & is heart worm negative. 

Buddy is currently fostered in the Tennessee. He will travel to his new home once he has been adopted. We use a weekly pet transport service to the northeast. Pick up is available in MD, PA, NJ, NY, CT, VT. www.petsllc.net

For the dogs adopted to the mid-west, we have a weekly trip to the Chicago area where they can be picked up. 
The next time they can be picked up in Chicago is Friday, February 5, 2021. 

Our primary source of funding comes from this adoption donation. This donation allows us to rescue other dogs in danger of being put to sleep, injured or sick dogs and dogs that have never known the comfort of a home.
Thank you for considering one of our rescue dogs.

animal.description:
Bonnie’s sad story has become a happy story!  This beautiful sweet girl will have a wonderful life from now on.  She is only one year old and happy and healthy.  She is spayed and current on all her vaccinations and is heartworm negative.  Many JRTs are very bouncy!!  But, Bonnie is not that way.  She is more the cuddle bug type.  Her two favorite dogs in her foster home are a 13 year old male JRT and a 6 month old mixed breed puppy.  Bonnie can be a little bit dog selective...she likes some male dogs, but not female dogs and no cats or kiddos (kids make her too nervous)  Her house manners are great.  Sleeping with you is what she really wants to do, but can go in her crate even though she does not like it.  Bonnie is small.  Her weight is about 12-13 pounds so she is very petite.  She likes to snoop around in the yard and hunt for bunnies and lizards.  Barking at squirrels is also fun.  Going for walks is fine too as long as it is not too far.  Her legs are short.  If you want a jogging/walking/biking/hiking partner she is probably not the girl for you.  All in all, Bonnie is a little moonbeam of a dog.  In order to adopt her you must be comfortable with someone coming to your home for a visit.  You also need a good vet  reference.  Your fence needs to be very secure.  No wrought iron.  No electronic fencing.  Bonnie was picked up stray once already, so we want to make sure her forever home has a fence that can contain her.  Her adoption fee is $275.  Please fill out the online application on www.RussellRescue.com  Her adopter must be able to drive to the San Antonio/Seguin, Texas area to get her.  Contact: jamesejolley@gmail.com


RussellRescue.com

Email: jamesejolley@gmail.com

animal.description:
PLEASE READ: The clinics are not open for viewing animals. Since we currently can't meet you in person, if you are interested in meeting this pet, please email information about yourself, family, residence and current/prior pet experience. If it is a good fit you will be emailed an application. Once that is approved, arrangements will be made for a meeting. Thanks for your understanding!

Mullis is an approximately 12 week old male Jack Russell (?) Mix who we believe should stay around the small side of the "medium" category as an adult. Unfortunately we don't know either parent so we can't say for sure what breed mix they are and ultimately what size they will be but this is our best guess. Mullis and his littermates were rescued from a Kentucky shelter when their time was up. His adoption fee is $399 and includes his neuter, vaccinations, microchip and routine labwork. Please email us to start the adoption process.

For puppies 6 months and younger you must live within 50 miles of Oswego, IL.

Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes: 
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*: 
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming 
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old) 
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt: 
If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

animal.description:
****Please do not message the rescue asking if this dog is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: 
*Age: 
*Current Weight: 
*Rescued from: 
*Adoption fee: $375 (plus $125 spay/neuter deposit, which is refundable when spay/neuter agreement is fulfilled)
*Health: up to date on required vaccines

______ was rescued from an area where there is an abundance of homeless dogs, and not a lot of shelter space for them to go while they wait for their forever homes. He/She will be arriving at SNARR's Adoption Center in Brewster, NY on ______ ready for adoption! To apply to adopt _______, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 
**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**

IMPORTANT: This dog has not yet been altered. For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a strictly-enforced signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
TO CONTACT WILLOW’S FOSTER HOME, EMAIL heelersarethestorm@gmail.com
DO NOT USE the Petfinder form. Inquiries do not reach us.

Meet Willow: 
2.5-year-old Female Blue Heeler, Spayed, 40 lbs.

Willow is a very gentle, sweet, happy Australian Cattle Dog (blue) that is not going to tell anyone about
her start in life. It is something that she chooses to forget now that she has learned that life can be fun,
safe, and people can be trusted. She is microchipped, crate trained (she loves to ‘crate up’), housebroken,
and knows ‘touch’ for games and treats.

Willow loves to ‘go sit on her bed’, loves to ‘find it’ referring to treat games to give some fun things to do
inside. Willow learns quickly and happily. She is a “Velcro girl”, so her recall is quite good, as she is never
more than a few feet away. Her favorite place to be is right by her foster Mom’s side! She also loves her
morning and afternoon naps. Willow loves belly rubs, soft pats and gentle touches. She is curious and
willing to try new things all the time. She is learning to catch treats in her mouth and is enjoying
mastering that skill.

She will need a very patient forever home that will allow Willow the time she needs, possibly several
weeks, to let her truly brave self to come out and trust her new people. This is so important for her – only
on Willow’s terms and very slowly, the trust will happen as she observes and gets used to her new
environment and new people.

She would love a home where she can be with her person 24/7- that is ideal for this lovely girl! Willow
does much better with women than men (please, no all-male homes for her). With patience and time, she
came to trust her foster Dad, but only since he was willing to let Willow decide when it would happen.
Now they are good buddies!

Willow would do best in a quiet country setting, without children. Fast movements, even by her trusted
people, can still be scary, but she is so happy and wants to have fun, and recovers nicely now. City streets,
cars, lots of people and strange sounds are not for this girl, so a quieter setting with a fenced yard would
be ideal for Willow.

She was Heartworm (HW) positive when she came into foster care with ACDRA and has been fully treated.
Her activity is still limited until her next HW test in April. She loves her leashed walks/hikes and is very
good on leash. She is up to date on vaccines and HW preventive.

She has been low to medium energy here at her foster home, but as she moves through her heartworm
limited activity period, she seems to want to run and play more (though not allowed until she slowly gets
back to normal activity once she receives a HW negative test), so classifying her as medium energy seems
best. She is quite interested in the deer on the other side of the fence, so medium prey drive also. She
would likely do well as an only dog, or have a respectful, low to medium energy dog friend. She does not
enjoy high energy dogs at all. She has not been around cats, but we feel that she may chase them. 

Willow is looking for her perfect forever home where she can be given the chance to grow on her own
terms - slowly. Then the sky is the limit for this beautiful young girl as she embarks on her best life and is
allowed to become a truly happy, trusting, funny, companion, and family member!

Willow is being fostered in Clinton, NJ.
Her foster Mom can be reached at: heelersarethestorm@gmail.com.

COMPLETE AN APPLICATION
http://www.acdra.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Meet Jingle! Jingle is a 2-3 year old male yellow Labrador Retriever. He got out of the shelter around Christmas and went to wonderful fosters of ours who have 4 other dogs if their own. He gets along well with all and has had no issues. He is described by the foster as very calm, sweet and laid back. He’s not your typical full of energy lab. He does play and would be a great walking companion but doesn’t need a high energy household. 

Jingle is house and crate trained. He is not a huge fan of the crate but will go in it. He is shy around strangers and takes a bit to warm up before getting used of them. He would be fine as an only dog or with a calmer more laid back dog that doesn’t want to play with him non-stop. He has also been around the fosters young grand children. 

Jingle is up to date on all shots, recently neutered and micro-chipped. He is current on monthly flea, tick and heartworm prevention. He is available locally for meet and greets. He can also be adopted out of state- a transport fee would apply in addition to his adoption fee.

animal.description:
[IF DOGS ARE POSTED THAT MEANS THEY ARE AVAILABLE! PLEASE DO NOT EMAIL ASKING IF THEY ARE AVAILABLE. IF THEY ARE POSTED, THEY ARE AVAILABLE — IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN SETTING UP A MEET AND GREET, SUBMIT AN APPLICATION THECANTUFOUNDATION.ORG ]

It’s your new homie: Romy!
Hi! I’m Romy! I’m seven months old and I’m a female German shepherd mix. I’m fully vaccinated AND I’m spayed, so all my medical needs are taken care of! I’m pretty small: only 26 pounds! I’m smart, too. I’m already potty trained and I know how to walk on a leash! I can be a little timid when I go for walks, but I do well despite that. I’m not crate trained though.
I was rescued with my sister, Michelle, in Mexico. We were part of an extremely friendly pack of dogs! As you can probably guess, I’m friendly with dogs of any size. I’m currently being fostered in a home with three other dogs, and we all get along! I’m not sure if I get along with cats or kids yet though, because I haven’t met either one yet. But maybe we can give it a try!
My foster momma says I’m the perfect little girl. She says I’m so gentle and calm; I’m the sweetest pup and I love to cuddle; it’s my favorite thing in the world! I also love to play and nibble on toys. If my foster momma could describe me in three words they would be “sweet,” “calm,” and “loveable.” My ideal home would have another dog that I can romp around in the yard with. I love to have company. I don’t show any signs of separation anxiety, so I’ll be fine with my owner coming and going, but I’m used to always having another canine companion with me. I’m pretty much the perfect dog, if I do say so myself! If you think I sound like a good fit for your family, you can apply to adopt me at http://www.thecantufoundation.org/adopt.html. My adoption fee is $500. I can’t wait to meet you!

animal.description:
Meet Cali! This gal is a 70lbs lab-staffy-hound mix at 8 years young!

She’s exceptionally friendly with people and spectacular with dogs. The shelter used her to test other dogs social skills due to her tolerant nature. Because of her gentle demeanor, we think she would be great in a home with kids. She’s a star companion dog, well- mannered, and a dream on leash.

She would do best in a home where people will be around often, leaving her home alone for no more than 4 hours on a regular basis

animal.description:
Foster location: Kuna ID
Breed: Saint Bernard
DOB: 4/25/2014
Size: 180 pounds
Adoption Fee: $200.00
Spayed, Vaccinated, Microchipped


If interested you MUST complete the Adoption Application: http://fuzzypawzrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application-2/


Wow where to even start with this girl! Ester came to Fuzzy Pawz Rescue when her family could no longer care for her. She had one of the worst cases of Cherry Eye we had ever seen; 3 surgeries later she is finally better! She doesn’t have full site and is a bit deaf but she is one healthy and happy girl.


This gentle giant has become a BIG part of her foster family! Ester has put up with teens running in/out of the house, sharing with the other dogs and a cat and all manner of chaos. She has helped with watering (drool) the house plants, mopping the floors (drool and fluff) and contributing (dog hair) to the vacuum. 


She's great to snuggle with while reading or watching television – and will do anything for a belly rub. She is a calm, good-natured dog but can get playful at times – so it’s nice if she has easy access to a yard with space to move or just to stretch out in. Because she has no idea how big she is - she can be a bit much for small children accidentally knocking them over or to be honest she can knock over a full grown adult. Be warned she gets crazy puppy antics when you come home for the day (it is delightful!)


She’s not going to be a jogging companion but loves to take a stroll around the neighborhood and is a big fan of car rides. 


She is house-trained, know basic commands, good on a leash, does not bark unless there is a reason to. Ester would be a great choice for the person or family who would like a large but gentle loving dog. Due to her size no kids in her home under the age of 10.

Since we currently can't meet you in person, if you are interested in meeting this pet, please email information about yourself, family, residence and current/prior pet experience. If it is a good fit you will be emailed an application. Once that is approved, arrangements will be made for a meeting. Thanks for your understanding!

Einstein is an approximately 12 week old male Jack Russell (?) Mix who we believe should stay under 25 lbs as an adult. He is the smallest pup in this litter. Einstein has a short naturally docked tail. Unfortunately we don't know either parent so we can't say for sure what breed mix they are and ultimately what size they will be but this is our best guess. Einstein and his littermates were rescued from a Kentucky shelter when their time was up. His adoption fee is $399 and includes his neuter, vaccinations, microchip and routine labwork. Please email us to start the adoption process.

For puppies 6 months and younger you must live within 50 miles of Oswego, IL.

Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes: 
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*: 
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming 
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old) 
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt: 
If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

Martini is a 10 week old puppy in search of his forever Valentine! He is well socialized, loves to play, and is so sweet he may actually cause cavities. Martini is around 10 pounds and is ready to start his potty and obedience training. His hobbies are wrestling with his mom, eating, making mischief, and being adorable. 

This puppy is neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccinations and current on flea/tick and heartworm preventative.

The adoption fee is $550 if your adoption is prepaid prior to your pup's arrival. An additional $50 will be charged on puppies that are picked up from our Southbury CT adoption center, adopted at an event or foster home. This additional fee is necessary in order to comply with CT HB 5368.

If you are an MA resident, your new family member is required to go through a mandatory 48 hour quarantine period at the Woburn MA isolation facility. Your new family member will be dropped off by our transport on Thursday and will be ready for you to pick him/her up on Saturday between 12pm - 2pm. An additional $100 fee will be added for any dogs picked up from the Woburn MA quarantine facility. This additional fee is necessary in order to comply with MA Order 405-CD-12 and Order 1-AHO-05.

TO APPLY PLEASE GO TO www.cprdogs.com. If your application was successfully submitted you will get a confirmation. 

After receipt of your application, an adoption counselor will then be in touch to answer your questions about this pup, discuss the adoption process and get the ball rolling! If you have not heard from one of our volunteers within 5 days of submitting your application, please email mollibo@gmail.com.

Paris was turned in to us by her owner after the owner's husband died and she wasn't able to care for Paris on her own. Paris is 8 years old and weighs about 12 pounds. When she came to us, she was obese at 15 pounds, but we've been able to get her to lose a few pounds. She could still lose a couple of pounds, but she's feeling much better. Paris is very sweet and loving. She walks well on leash and travels well in the car. She does good with pottying outside as long as you take her out regularly. Paris is a beautiful chocolate pom. She had been shaved when we got her, but her hair is growing back and getting long again. Paris is spayed, microchipped, and had a dental. Her shots have been updated and she's heartworm negative. Paris is ready to find her forever home.

In order to adopt, you need to send an e-mail to rescue@secondchancepoms.org asking for an application.  After you send this back, we will check references and someone will visit you in your home to discuss adoption.  We ask a donation of $425 for adults, which includes an applicable Texas sales tax, and $475 for puppies, which includes an applicable Texas sales tax.  This covers shots, spay/neuter, and any medical treatment, such as de-worming. We do not ship our pomeranians, but an out-of-state adoption can still happen if the adopter comes to the Houston, TX area to pick up their pom.

Haylee is about 3 years old, weighs about 4 pounds, female, Chihuahua, spayed (TBA), vaccinated, microchipped. She is very scared and would benefit from being in a quiet foster home with someone who is patient and can teach her not all humans hurt. Once she warms up she is very playful and friendly.

She is only available for foster at this time until she has been fully vetted, i.e., spayed, vaccinated, microchipped, and received a clean bill of health. She has a mammary tumor which will be removed and biopsied.

animal.description:
Looking for a handsome, sweet and loving boy to add to your family? Then check out Chance (aka Buddy)! He is a Doberman mix probably around 3-4 years old but still acts like a clumsy, goofy puppy with his long legs. He was found as a stray clearly not well cared for, but now he is living in a loving foster home learning all kinds of new things about how to be a well-balanced pup. He loves to play and run around in the yard but also can kick back and relax next to you on the couch for hours. His foster family says he is a true diamond in the rough! Everything was new to Chance... walking on a leash, potty training, riding in the car, basic commands, you name it. But he is a fast learner and really wants to please his humans so he is learning very quickly what it's like to be a loving, respectful member of the family. He will require an owner with patience that will continue his training and keep him active both physically and mentally. Although Chance currently lives with other dogs, we feel his ideal home will have no other dogs or small kids since he is such a big boy and still working on his boundaries. This stunning dog has so much potential and will make an incredible best buddy for the right human(s). If you want to take a chance on Chance, get your application in today!

If you are interested in adopting, please visit the I.C.A.R.E. Dog Rescue website and complete an adoption application: www.icaredogrescue.org/ready-to-adopt

Adoption fee includes: spay/neuter shots up to date micro-chip fecal and vet checkClick here to watch a video of Chance.

PLEASE READ: You MUST visit https://www.save-a-mutt.org/adoption-application/ to fill out an application and get pre-approved before meeting any Save-A-Mutt dogs. We are a foster based rescue. There is no facility to visit. 


**We are asking for a home with German Shepherd experience for Klink**
Klink is a very sweet boy who is ready for a family of his own.  He would love a home with a fenced yard where he can run and play whenever he wants.  His leash manners are lacking so he will need a person who is strong and ready to teach him what's expected while out on walks.  

Klink loves people of all ages but, because of his size, we are asking for home without children under 12.  This big boy wants to be the only pet in the home where he can soak up all the love and affection that his people have to give.  A home with no other dogs and no cats will be required.

Klink was recently neutered and has an eyelid margin mass removed.  He is doing great and ready to go home.  Klink is 10 years old and weighs 119 pounds.

Adoption fee is $150.00 + $100.00 refundable training deposit to be refunded upon completion of training course.
Save-A-Mutt is a registered 501c3.

Please note, we have approximately a 300 mile adoption radius. We don’t ship dogs.  Once approved you must pick them up in Snohomish County, WA *Due to the Border Closure to Canada - we are currently not accepting Canadian Adoption Applications*. Sorry.

Since we currently can't meet you in person, if you are interested in meeting this pet, please email information about yourself, family, residence and current/prior pet experience. If it is a good fit you will be emailed an application. Once that is approved, arrangements will be made for a meeting. Thanks for your understanding!

Crick is an approximately 12 week old male Jack Russell (?) Mix who we believe may be slightly larger than his brothers as an adult, but will likely be on the small end of "medium" category. Unfortunately we don't know either parent so we can't say for sure what breed mix they are and ultimately what size they will be but this is our best guess. Crick and his littermates were rescued from a Kentucky shelter when their time was up. His adoption fee is $399 and includes his neuter, vaccinations, microchip and routine labwork. Please email us to start the adoption process.

For puppies 6 months and younger you must live within 50 miles of Oswego, IL.

Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes: 
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*: 
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming 
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old) 
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt: 
If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

Rory is about 9 months old, weighs about 8 pounds, male, terrier/mix, neuter (TBA), vaccinated, microchipped. He does well with other dogs and once he comes around he is playful. 

He is only available for foster at this time until he has been fully vetted, i.e., neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, and received a clean bill of health.

We cannot guarantee any of our available dogs are "hypoallergenic" if you have allergies please consider this before applying. Please also know there is not "hypoallergenic" dog, only low shedding.
All the information we have about them is in their description.

animal.description:
This sweet little girl is Grace! She is about 9 weeks old and is a typical, playful puppy. She will probably be a 40-60 lb adult. We do not know what her breeds are, just that she is sweet natured. 

Adopters must live within a 100-mile radius of Joliet, IL to be considered. The adoption fee is $425 with $100 refundable deposit added.  This covers all shots, spay/neutering and microchip.

To be considered for this dog. Please fill out an application here: https://www.pawsup4rescue.org/dog-cat-applicaiton

Our adoption process typically takes from one to two weeks. When you find an animal you are interested in, we ask that you fill out an application as a first step so we can determine if your family is a good fit for the animal. If you are, then we will contact you to arrange a time for you and your family to meet the animal so you can decide if it is a good fit. If you currently have dogs, we require that the dogs be present at the meeting to make sure it's a good fit all around. Once compatibility is determined, we move on to the paperwork and finalizing the adoption. 

If the meet is not a good fit, we will keep your application on file for up to 1 year and we will gladly consider your family for another dog. 

Follow us on FACEBOOK: www.Facebook.com/PawsUp4Rescue/ 
and on INSTAGRAM: www.Instagram.com/Paws_Up_4_Rescue/

animal.description:
Rambo is an 11 week old Pitbull Mix. He is a very happy and playful boy. Rambo is learning to sit and play fetch. He is also working on his house training, but with the cold weather he gets cold pretty fast and wants to come back in sooner then he normally would. 
When Rambo came to us he was pretty skinny and had bald patches on his head caused by Demodectic Mange. Mange usually occurs in animals with immature immune system and it allows for an overgrowth of the normal mites on the skin. This can causes bald patches and flakey skin. Mange can be contagious to other dogs with compromised immune systems. Rambo is currently being treated and his hair and skin are looking much better. It will take at least 3 months for the Mange to be under control. Mange is not contagious to people or healthy animals.
Rambo's ideal home according to him would have another dog to play with and a family that loves to play fetch and snuggle. When it comes to kids, Rambo would be happy with bigger kids to play with. 

Please let us know if you have any questions about Rambo.

animal.description:
Labrador Retrievers are the #1 Favorite Dog Breed in America. Franz is an excellent example of a Lab and Catahoula mix. He is the perfect all-around family pet for any family.
Franz has thick soft sable fur with unique white markings. He is inquisitive, friendly and soooo handsome and playful. Franz is people-oriented. He will make you laugh and feel good and fill your Life with Joy. As an adult we foresee he will present a commanding presence!
Franz and his siblings were born around December 9th to a smaller-sized (approx 40-45 lbs) Labrador Retriever mix mother and a Catahoula father. The puppies were left behind when their elderly owner was hospitalized. His granddaughter rescued the puppies to find them good homes. Franz came to us in a good condition. He received his first set of puppy vaccinations and dewormer. On 02/2, Franz weighed 7.5-lbs.
Franz is looking for his Fur-ever home - Is That YOU? EMAIL us for more information about the adoption process and to SCHEDULE a time to meet this Handsome Boy! Thank you for seeking to adopt a rescued dog! :)

animal.description: MEET TYSON!! This handsome 90 pound guy is Tyson! Tyson is a 5-year-old neutered male pit bull mix who came to us when his owner passed away. This friendly goofball is looking for an active home that can provide him with plenty of exercise, as he could benefit from losing a few pounds :) He is strong and can play a little rough sometimes so ideally he would need an experienced dog owner and to go to a teen/adult only home. He could potentially go home to another dog that can handle his high energy self. He would prefer to not live with cats though. He loves running around our yard and rolling around for belly rubs! If you think you are this friendly guy's forever home please fill out the adoption inquiry form for our Boston location below! This animal is currently up to date on all vaccinations, has been neutered, microchipped and been seen by our vet team. If you are interested in adopting this animal, please fill out our web form, available here: Boston Adoption Interest Form You can expect a response to your inquiry from a member of our adoption staff within 48 hours of completing this form. Due to our high volume of inquiries, please refrain from calling unless that time frame has passed. If needed, you can reach the Boston shelter at 617-426-9170 x604. The Animal Rescue League of Boston is currently operating by appointment only Tuesday-Sunday 1pm-6pm. Our Adoption Forward process will start with a phone conversation. Also, be sure to check out our: * ARL Website * ARL Twitter * ARL Facebook * ARL Instagram

animal.description: Woof, woof! I'm so excited you're thinking about adopting a new fur-ever family member! Here are a few things that may help you with your big decision. First, dogs just want to be happy and feel loved. Living inside and being a part of the family is really important to us. A lot of the things you need as humans to stay happy and healthy, us dogs need too. We depend on you for things like vet visits, nutritious food, clean water, social and play time with people and other pets, training classes, toys, and of course, lots of love and attention! Regular baths, nail trims and grooming help us to look and feel our best, while monthly flea and heartworm prevention help us to stay healthy. Did you know that depending on our size and breed, dogs can live up to 20 years? Just think of the wonderful life we could have together!

If you want to become a foster parent, fill out our application here: https://volgistics.com/ex/portal.dll/ap?ap=6848568 The dog/cat adoption fee, which is normally $60 unless we are having a special, includes spay or neuter, MICROCHIP, age-appropriate shots and health check. The shelter is at 2811 S.E. 29th St., phone # 297-3100. Use pet's ID # when inquiring. Special Adoption Fees: In the following cases, the adoption fee is $30-if more than one pet is adopted, if the pet is 4 years of age or older, if the pet has been in the adoption center more than 2 weeks, and if the pet is a 'special needs' pet.

animal.description:
Duke is a big goofy boy who loves playing and doing things! A few other words that our staff have used in describing him...energetic, green, smart and nice. 

Although raised in a home from 8 weeks old, he grew and grew in size and energy and his owners felt like he would have a better life if he had people that could give him the activity and attention he craves. He still has a lot of puppy in him and he is just learning how to learn, so he is looking for a partner or family who can help him grow up and become a well-mannered nice boy instead of an unruly wild child. He has all the qualities needed for the former, but runs the risk of remaining the latter, if left to his own devices. 

Our handlers have been working with him from the ground up, since he didn't come to us with any discernable skills--he is smart and he wants to please and if he is able to continue on with training and obedience, he has the potential to be a very nice dog indeed.

He is pleased with people and can be very friendly and playful, but with dogs he can be over-zealous in his excitement. He will need some help with proper canine social skills because he has none at this point in his young life.

Duke was disqualified from continuing on in our search dog training program because of indications of elbow dysplasia on his x-rays. The search work that our dogs train for requires lots of high-impact physical activity (jumping up and down from heights, running on uneven surfaces, lateral moves and other activities hard on joints). He shows no outward signs and other than limiting high impact activities, he would benefit from lots of physical activity such as hiking, walking, swimming, toy play and any low-impact dog sport.

This big sweet goof is always looking for a good time and wants to have it with you!

Duke is 1 year and 2 months old and weighs 68 pounds. He is neutered and up to date on vaccinations.

animal.description:
lf you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire (http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/) and e-mail questions to Lauren at htar.lauren@gmail.com

Effective March 18, 2020 all animals available for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. Our Adoption Center public hours are suspended until further notice. Cats dwelling at Crumbs & Whiskers can be met by approved adopters only by appointment. Please submit an online application and an adoption coordinator will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience and we hope to keep saving lives during this difficult time.

Sirius is a very special lab that grew up on a meat farm in South Korea. When he came to us, he was shut down, would not make eye contact, and would not leave his crate. With the tireless work of his amazing foster, he has blossomed and come so far. That being said, he will still require a very special and patient home that understands he may regress some but are willing to continue to work with him on his confidence. 

Sirius requires a home with another confident dog and a fenced in yard. No apartments/no urban settings. 

Things to know about Sirius: 
1- He is pee pad trained and also housetrained. He will probably need a few days to decompress before he is ready to go outside. However, he doesn't tell you when he needs to go so he still needs to be taken out every few hours. 
2- He is crate trained 
3- He is not fully leash trained but after a gentle tug, he will walk with you for a short distance. It is preferred that he goes to a home with a fence. 
4- He has zero aggression and loves to cuddle and play at night. 
5- He is great with kids and other dogs.
6- He gets scared of loud noises but if you introduce things to him slowly he will adapt very quickly. 
7- He is not picky with food. He loves chew toys.
8- He does not bark unless he is playing (rarely). 
9- He doesn't mind being groomed. (Bath, brush, and nail clipped) 

Adoption Coordinator: Lauren T
Location: Foster Home
The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee DOES INCLUDE spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide a 30-minute phone consult with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert advice and guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program/

animal.description:
*We are not hosting adoption events at Petco for the public at this time*
We are currently very busy and have over 100 applications to review and on file. Thank you for your patience! We are working to find everyone a companion. 

His names explains it all! 

Happy is an active, and friendly 1 year old lab mix. 

This goofy boy loves to make dog and people friends! He would be a wonderful adventure, and hiking parter. Happy boy is searching for his forever companion! He is house and kennel trained.

If you are interested in adopting the first step is to fill out an adoption application on our website aaanimalrescue.org. We are currently very busy! Please reach out to allaboardanimalrescue@gmail.com if you have an approved application on file! Please fill out an adoption application on our website if you are ready to adopt! 

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this difficult time! We are on a mission to find everyone companions, we will continue to rescue dogs weekly! We update our page every Monday evening. We are not currently hosting any Petco adoption events for the public. We will be hosting meet/greet adoption appointments!


Breed and size disclosure: As a rescue all of our dogs come to us from high-kill shelters or other rescues, so we do not get a lot of background or information on these dogs. We occasionally receive the mother with the puppies, but in most cases both parents are unknown. Because of this we do not know the full breeding of the dogs. We are required to list the dogs based on the breeds provided to us on their records, but they are all mixed breeds as far as we know, and we cannot guarantee the actual breeds of any of these dogs. Since the full breeding of the dogs is unknown we can also only give you an educated guess on the full-grown size of the dogs. All of the current information we have on the dogs is listed in their bio above. More information may be available at our adoption event, since a lot of the fosters turn in report cards on how the dog has done in their care when they drop them off. 

Adoption Process: If you are interested in adopting from us, the first step of our adoption process is to fill out an application online at http://aaanimalrescue.org/adoption_app.html. It takes us 24-48 hours to process your application and get back to you, via email. Applications turned in Friday afternoon or Saturday morning will not be processed since we are preparing for or at our adoption event. We do have applications on site at our events, but are not always able to approve them at that time and many of the dogs will already have holds on them, so we suggest you fill out an application prior to attending an adoption event. We can place a hold on one dog per approved applicant after a deposit fee has been received, please do not ask to hold a dog if you have not turned in an application and been approved, for the first hour of our adoption event, so that they can get the first chance to meet and hopefully adopt that dog. After the first hour of the event all dogs are available on a first come, first serve basis. If you already have an approved application on file, there will just be more paperwork and the adoption fee at the event, but you will be able to take home the dog/puppy that day. Since we are foster based and do not have a location, our dogs are only available to meet at our events, unless otherwise noted.

animal.description:
PLEASE READ: The clinics are not open for viewing animals. Since we currently can't meet you in person, if you are interested in meeting this pet, please email information about yourself, family, residence and current/prior pet experience. If it is a good fit you will be emailed an application. Once that is approved, arrangements will be made for a meeting. Thanks for your understanding!

Bonnie is a sweet and playful German Shepherd puppy looking for her forever home. She was surrendered by an owner who could not handle her. She is 5.5 months old. Bonnie needs a home with no kids or only kids 12 and up, as she nips playfully pretty hard and is still working on manners. She does excellent in doggie daycare and plays very well with the other dogs, taking corrections nicely. She would benefit from a home with shepherd experience who would be interested in pursuing training for her and continue to keep her active and socialized. Bonnie's adoption fee is $429 and includes her spay, microchip, vaccinations and routine labwork. Please email us to start the adoption process.

For adoptions of puppies 6 months old and younger, you must reside within 50 miles of Oswego, IL



Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes: 
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*: 
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming 
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old) 
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt: 
If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

animal.description:
Foster location:  Meridian ID 
Breed:  German Wire Hair/Heeler
Age:  9 years 
Adoption Fee:  $100.00

Spayed, Vaccinated, Microchipped

Adoption Application:  http://fuzzypawzrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application-2/

This pretty girl came to Fuzzy Pawz Rescue when her human dad’s life changed and he was no longer able to care for her.

Patches is a super sweet easy going girl who really just wants to spend time with her people.  We have found that she is much happier in the company of men – she’s fine with women but gravitates to men.  She would not do well with kids under 15 and would prefer to have a quieter lifestyle.

She enjoys napping on the couch with her person; slow walks around the block and playing with her Frisbee or a ball.   She is house trained and will also use a dog door and has great house manners. She doesn’t care for car rides but tolerates them since most trips are going to the park for a walk. She is afraid of fireworks and thunderstorms but deals with them better now as she has gotten older.

Patches is okay with other dogs, she has lived with one successfully in the past; however while in foster care we have found that she can be a bit grumpy around other dogs.  Patches will also chase cats.  Honestly we believe she would prefer to be the only dog or to live with a submissive male.

At her age it is not surprising that she has a bit of arthritis in her senior years; but she still likes to get up and go – it’s just a bit slower now. Patches does have a food sensitivity and needs to eat special dog food, if not on the specialized food she gets ear infections.  She is eating Hills Z/D dry dog food and Iams lamb & rice pate from a can.

If you are looking for a sweet and very loyal dog then Patches will be just the right fit.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Name: Hondo

DOB: 12/24/13

Weight: 15 lb

Adoption Fee: 325.00

Hello,

My name's Hondo, but my foster dad thinks Shadow would be more appropriate since he can't go anywhere without me, even outside. Being from TX, you think the snow would be a bother, but the only thing that keeps me from going on longer walks is my chilly paws; I may need to get used to booties!

At 15 pounds, I fit perfectly on most laps, so I hope you don't mind. Docs think I'm 7 years old, so I'm young enough to appreciate long walks AND long naps.

We should start our relationship with total honesty; I was an owner surrender due to a biting incident, but I've been on my best behavior since arriving in Minnesota. Slow introductions are important, but a household with small children may not be the best option.

I've had some accidents in the house, but that could be the result of a few different factors, so my fosters are cutting me some slack.

I sleep all the way through the night once I've done the required 5 minutes of spinning and arranging of blankets in my crate.

I've only been at my fosters for a couple days, but my tail is already wagging and I'm playing with my foster brother, so I think I'll get along okay with other dogs, but I'm not sure about cats. I also have mixed feelings about my tail. I chase it, but its curliness has made it very elusive.

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

Please check out our website,

www.ruffstartrescue.org

for more details and additional pictures on any of our animals!

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies:

http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Hi there! My name is Daffodil and I am a 3 month old boarder collie mix! I am a snuggly girl who had a very rough start to my life. My siblings and I were turned into animal control because our previous owner stopped feeding us. We were kept in a dirt lot and were slowly withering away. lucky for us, a good samaritan called animal control to report us. The bad news is that because we were in such poor body condition, we were immediately placed on the euthanasia list. Luckily our rescuers came just in time to save us! Now that we have gotten up t a healthy weight, and have gotten the green light from the vet, we are ready to meet you! 

My foster parents call me Daffy! I am the sweetest girl you will ever meet. All I want s to be snuggled and pet by my humans! I am a happy pup who would be more than comfortable spending our days relaxing on the couch and sleeping in front of the fire place! I get along great with other dogs and have also done wonderfully with the cats! I am great with children too! My foster parents say that I am required to go home to a house with a yard for me to run and play in! I would also LOVE to have another pup sibling to rough and tumble with! If you think thatI would be a good match for your family, send AZ Rez-cue an email so we can get together!

PLEASE INCLUDE: 
Tell us about your family! 
Do you have other animals at home? 
Do you rent or own your home? Does it have a fenced yard or park option? 
Have you owned animals in the past? If so, what kind? 
Do you have any questions for us? 

Emails that do not include this information will not be considered, as our adoption process required this knowledge to move forward! Thank you for your interest in one of our Rez-cues!

animal.description:
Olive, Date of Birth-12-31-2018, is part of a seizure from a breeder. Dogs from breeders are seldom housetrained or socialized.  Olive is very sweet, seems to love dogs and people, will give kisses, but is shy, so fast ,movements scare he. She has shown no aggression, loves food and treats, is stocky like an Australian Shepherd, and has a Aussie tail, but her personality is definitely Poodley. She is known as an AussieDoodle. She slept quietly in her crate last night, her first night here. She did not soil her crate, which is great news.
She goes out willingly and comes in willingly.  When I pet her face she stands up on her hind feet. She weighs about 25 lbs., is definitely a chow hound so her weight needs to be watched, and fed appropriate amounts or she would gain very quickly.

She walks ok on a leash, but needs practice. She reacts best to a soft and loving voice.  She won't be placed with small kids since I don't know if she has been around kids, but 12 and up should be ok if the child has been taught to respect animals and treats her gently.

Olive's  adoption fee is $300.00. She is fully vetted, spayed, micro chipped, had a dental and her ears were cleaned and medicated. She doesn't like grooming, but will need a gentle groomer, because her hair grows like a Poodles. She especially doesn't like the clippers on her face. The breeder seldom groomed/shaved her.

If interested in adopting Olive, e-mail me and tell me about your home, yard, how long you are gone from home for work, play, and your family, other dogs and kids.

e-mail- heartofamerica99@aol.com

animal.description:
TO CONTACT THE FOSTER HOME, emailTulips1990@gmail.com.
DO NOT use the Petfinder form. Inquiries don't reach us.

Hey!  Whats your name!?  Mine in Benny Benson!
I’m searching for a forever family to call my own, so I never have to be given up again!
Don’t worry, I am fixed, fully vetted and about 1.5 years old! Just enough of a puppy still but ready to mature in the next year or so!

What kind of things do you like to do for fun?  I’m a good amount of energy and like to romp around, but boy do I know how to sit back and relax at home!  I’m still getting use to toys, not sure what to do with them much, but I LOVE treats! You ever seen anyone else do the two-step hoppity hop over treats and food time? NO!? Well, I can show ya!  I’m addicted to belly rubs and wanting to be petted. I’ll literally melt into your arms or lap if you think you’d like to give the belly a rubbin’ ! I like to keep it on the low-key and not talk about it much, but I wasn’t treated very nicely in my prior life, so moving your hands too quick over my head or towards me may make me duck a bit, but the most dangerous thing I’d do back is give you major puppy eyes.  Due to this, young children may not be the best fit for me so I think I’d be happier with children 10+ who are dog savvy and who know how to respect boundaries, should the need ever arise.  

My foster mum says I go into new environments scared and nervous, so I don’t really show much of my personality right off the bat.  When I first moved in with her, I ignored every kitty (out of 5!) in the house and settled quickly and quietly into my crate.  After a few days, I started to feel better and decided, you know what, I think chasing a kitty will be fun!  I also did this to mums horses and after a few days I wanted to try and taste one!  So, mum says she think it’ll be best if there were no kitties in my new forever home, just to be on the safe side.  I’m great with other dogs! Personally, I’d say I am more on the submissive side when interacting with new pups, but I haven’t met any dominant dogs yet.  I haven’t felt the need to resource guard anything like food or toys around people or dogs- mum says I’m awesome like that! I sleep well through the night in a crate- sometimes I can be a bit "whiney" mum says but I settle easily with a crate cover if needed. I go on car rides very nicely! I'm pretty quiet and don't seem to get car sick. I would make an AWESOME barn hunt dog! You know, the thing where I have to search hay bales for the mice? Mum says I seem like a natural with it!  What I’d love best is a relatively quiet but active family with a great fenced yard that I can continue to romp around happily and follow you around the house. Mum says I am way too SWEET to not get the best life possible! Can’t wait to meet ya!

Located in Zebulon, NC. For questions, please contact Tulips1990@gmail.com.

COMPLETE AN APPLICATION

animal.description:
Foster location:  Boise ID
Breed:  Min Pin/Chihuahua
Born:  May 2020 (best guess)
Adoption Fee:  $200.00
Spayed, Vaccinated, Microchipped

If interested you MUST complete the Adoption Application:  http://fuzzypawzrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application-2/

Sweet little Delilah is a bundle of energy who came to Fuzzy Pawz from the shelter where she was not doing well.
She needed a quiet home to deal with her insecurity and gain some confidence. She can be very timid and apprehensive around strangers, but patience and understanding will be rewarded with a very loyal and sweet girl. It will take her some time and maybe several visits from people before she will be comfortable with your regular guests so a quiet home without a lot of visitors would be ideal for her. Please no children under 15. 
Delilah is fantastic on leash and the only issue you might have is her giving a little woof or shying away when you encounter strangers otherwise she walks right beside you on leash. Regular walks and playtime will keep her happy and out of mischief as this girl has a lot of energy. Delilah gets along great with the other dogs in her foster home and loves to play with them. Cats are unknown. We think she would be a great candidate for someone who would like to train a small dog for agility. But just a loving home and daily walks will make her happy. She is definitely a lap dog and likes nothing better than to be near her human. 
She is crate trained and for the most part house trained. Some reinforcement when she first gets to her new home will be needed to show her where she goes and to learn her signs of knowing when she needs to go out as she is not very vocal about it. Once she is comfortable in her forever home that will probably improve. She knows a few basic commands but we strongly suggest a puppy class; it is an amazing way for you to bond and it will do wonders in boosting her confidence.

animal.description:
Johnny / Male / 9 Months / 60 lbs / Plott Hound Mix / Toronto

Meet Johnny! Johnny is described as eager to please, affectionate, energetic, friendly and excitable. He loves people and is happiest when receiving attention from his family or anyone who is willing! He loves long walks, playing in the snow, figuring out puzzles or chewing on his bones. Johnny is a true dream dog. He is more than ready for a loving and active family to call his own!

When walking down the street, Johnny shows interest in every person and dog that passes him. He will want to greet some people and can get a little bouncy and eager to give them kisses. He is very friendly but may need support and guidance on proper introductions. He doesn’t know his own size so may knock over small children by accident. He has also been known to nip in play, so even though he is always friendly, would do best with children that are ages 10+.

Still very much a puppy, Johnny needs to be provided with appropriate places to chew. If he gets bored, he will look for ways to entertain himself. If he can’t be supervised, he will need to be put in a puppy proofed space with safe things to chew. He is a very good boy and can usually be redirected as needed. Johnny does not like to be alone yet, and will be quite vocal when his foster Mom leaves. Adopters should have a flexible schedule to support him through his separation anxiety. When the radio is left on, he settles much quicker. With the right structure he will likely adjust quickly to a regular schedule.

Johnny is learning proper leash manners but will need continued support. He will pull when he sees/smells something and has selective hearing when he’s distracted. He can be reactive to other people and dogs, but it’s just because he wants to introduce himself. He needs a strong and patient handler willing to work with him on this. Generally, he just wants to play with dogs but has never been taught how to approach. He is on the higher side of medium energy, and will need a minimum of two long walks a day plus additional time in the backyard.

Johnny’s ideal home would be a detached house, with a fully fenced backyard. He can not be trusted in an unsecured space yet and will need supervision even in the backyard. He needs support with basic obedience and house manners in his forever home. Johnny would love to have another playful dog in the home, but it’s not essential as long as he gets consistent socialization. Johnny has a cat in his foster home and loves to play with her! Resident cats should be dog savvy and have adequate areas to escape if they need a break.

If you are interested in adopting Johnny please fill out an application at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/dog-adoption/

Johnny’s adoption fee is $850. To learn more about our adoption fees and process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/faq/.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Rocky!

Do you like other dogs? I get excited around other dogs and will need a dog that can tolerate my energy level! I will need to meet any potential new canine friends at the shelter before going home. 

What do you think about cats? I have no history with cats. I may do best in a cat free home.

So how do you feel about kids? I lived with kids around 10 and older. But I can play rough at times, so I would do best with older kids that can tolerate my energy and play style. 

What's your energy level like? I have a high energy level! 

What is it that staff and volunteers love about you? I am a super sweet guy with lots of energy! I do need some training and lots of exercise to become the best dog I can be! I have lived most of my life as an outside dog and I am most likely not house trained.

Is there anything else we should know about you? I am 8 months old and I weigh between 78-83 pounds.

I came into the shelter as a surrender and the above information is all recommendations based on my previous history and the behavior seen at the shelter. Expect to learn more about me after adoption.

It is unknown how this animal will do in their new home as all animals can be different with each person. It is important to take this into consideration when thinking about adopting and making sure you are prepared to work with any potential medical or behavior issues that occur after adoption.

My adoption fee includes my spay/neuter, current vaccinations, permanent microchip identification, certificate for a free veterinary exam, post-adoption support and more!

Thank you for taking the time to learn a little about me! If you think we would be a good match call and ask about me! I'm looking for my forever home and it could be with you!

ADOPTION INFORMATION: If you live in the city of Eugene or in Lane County you will be purchasing a dog license in addition to the adoption fee. You will get to choose between a one year, two year, or three year license.

animal.description: Athena is an adorable and shy little lady on the search for a special family and forever home. Athena is very nervous in new situations and when meeting new people, so she does best with slow and gentle introductions. Taking her on walks, gentle petting (but not too much at first), words of encouragement, and treats help Athena become more comfortable, though it may take her a little time to warm up! She would thrive in a home where her adopters can give her the time and space she needs to acclimate and be her advocate in new situations where she might be uncomfortable. Athena spent some time in a foster home, where we learned that she preferred to spend time in her safe spaces in the home, where she could always go to be comfortable. Once more familiar, Athena likes to stay close to her people. She also really enjoys walks, but in quiet, low-traffic areas because the traffic can be scary for her. When she is in the mood, she'll even pick up a toy or two! Athena did well meeting other dogs and might benefit from having a doggy buddy in her new home that can show her that things are not so scary. Athena would do best in a quiet home with older children and without a lot of visitors. If you are looking for a quiet and gentle girl to welcome into your family and give lots of TLC to, ask about adopting sweet Athena today!

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Chiquita! I'm an 8-year old 7-pound gal who loves to snuggle and burrow in soft things. I'm content to chill on your lap or next to you, and I love neck rubs. I sometimes have a bit of a wheeze, but the docs tell me that's not a problem. My foster mom tells me I sometimes snore so cutely...:). I warm quickly to new people, especially when they have a treat for me or let me climb into their lap. I like going on walks and am happy to go at a leisurely pace or pick up the speed if we're both in the mood! I like exploring my surroundings but I especially like being in the same room as you are. Oh, and I'm crate trained and potty trained :-). 

If you're interested in meeting me, reach out at jbshipley@me.com! 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZiI4IW1lyLo

animal.description:
7526
Judy is a most excellent dog! She has lovely manners with people of all ages including children and is housetrained, nondestructive, knows 'sit' and 'come' and is generally content to doze on her bed. She gives hugs and is an expert level snuggler. She knows she's royalty and would prefer to be admired properly as the only dog in the home. She was able to successfully co-exist with a dog savvy cat in her foster home, but she will chase a cat that runs from her, so any feline companions must have the confidence to stand their ground. She would prefer a living situation where she has a yard to spend time in or the space to avoid other dogs on walks. Judy loves hopping in the car and going for rides or coming to work with you if you're into that. For someone looking for a low-maintenance, pleasant companion, Judy would be an excellent choice.

For more information call (801) 261-2919 ext. 227 or drop by to meet her at our Murray location.

animal.description:
MY STORY: Rocky came to CBHS as an owner surrender.

AGE: Approximately 1 year.

TRICKS & COMMANDS: Sit, Lay Down

ABOUT ROCKY: Rocky is a very sweet and loving boy who'll give you all the doggy kisses! Rocky gets excited over the little things and his butt never stops wiggling.

Rocky loves soaking up any attention that you have to give and he'll sit by your side all day long for pets. He's very gentle and would make a great family dog. A yummy treat or a squeaky toy will really get his tail moving, and he'll happily sit for either of them. Rocky adores going on walks, but is a strong boy that could use a little help learning restraint and good walking manners. 

Rocky would be happy to meet any other 4-legged or 2-legged friends that live in the home.

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, vaccinations, worming, microchip, and a start on flea/tick prevention.

For more information, please call CBHS adoptions at 319-232-6887 or email at adoptioncounselor@yahoo.com.
