animal.description:
Miss Betty Sue is ready for her close-up. She has been the most devoted mom and is now ready to have a home and family of her own. She likes to keep her area extra clean and tidy. She has requested a family that will dote on her and include her in all the best activities. Betty Sue is a little package just bursting at the seems with love. 

Betty Sue currently weighs around 10 pounds.  She does well with other dogs, after a proper introduction.  

We require a non-refundable $20 adoption application fee. Farm Friends Rescue often receives more adoption applications than we have dogs in our program. We are a team of volunteers and processing those applications takes time and resources. Placing one of our dogs into a home is a responsibility that we take seriously. Our goal is to find the best forever family for each and every dog. By charging this small fee, we will ensure that only the most committed potential adopters start the process.

animal.description:
Meet Rocky!
Rocky is a sweet 60lb 5 year old Heeler/Rotti mix.  If you knew Rocky, you would not believe his breed makeup as he possesses no traits of a Heeler or a Rotti!  He is not hyper or super active, in fact he is a more low key and calm boy.  That could be due, in part, to his age, but his personality is also fantastic!  He is sweet as pie, loves the 8 other dogs he is currently living with (one in particular named Sara who is a border collie and is his BFF) and he loves kids.  Although Rocky hasn't been living with cats, he has zero prey drive and wouldn't hurt a fly so we know he would be fine with them.  Rocky is housetrained and fine in a crate, but does not need one as he has great house manners.  Rocky's only issue is that he is a very shy boy so we think he would probably do best in a forever home where there is another dog to provide him with a little confidence and a patient owner who will give him some time to settle into his new surroundings.  We would also like for Rocky to have a physically fenced yard where he can roam freely off leash.

Rocky is neutered, healthy and ready to head to his forever home in New England.  If you live in CT, NJ, NY or PA and are looking for the sweetest most submissive dog ever, please complete an application on our website!  www.asecondchanceforziva.org

Leo is an approximate 5 month shepherd mix expected to be 45-55lbs when full grown. He’s a forward but smart puppy needing someone willing to continue socialization, exposure, and training.

Because he was found at 4 weeks and spent his early months without other pups, Leo has been catching up on socialization in foster care where he is meeting many dogs! Leo needs to go to a home with a teacher dog (a balanced mature dog) who can show him the ropes.

Dog experience during adult-life is required, along with willingness and time to raise a puppy. No children under 14 years of age in the home.

Leo is crate training, leash training and potty training in foster. He is neutered and up to date on shots.

Applicants fulfilling the aforementioned requirements can inquire, and/or set up a meeting with Leo, by filling out application (copy and paste link): https://bluemandog.org/adoption-application/

We adopt our dogs in the greater LA area and nearby cities. Our adoption procedure and fees are described in our online adoption application.

animal.description:
Hi there! My name is Dandelion and I am a 3 month old boarder collie mix! I am a spunky girl who had a very rough start to my life. My siblings and I were turned into animal control because our previous owner stopped feeding us. We were kept in a dirt lot and were slowly withering away. lucky for us, a good samaritan called animal control to report us. The bad news is that because we were in such poor body condition, we were immediately placed on the euthanasia list. Luckily our rescuers came just in time to save us! Now that we have gotten up t a healthy weight, and have gotten the green light from the vet, we are ready to meet you! 

I am a sweet and playful girl that would love nothing more than a human to play with and a soft couch to relax on! I am a very friendly and outgoing girl and I know that I will be the perfect addition to any family! I get along great with other dogs and have also done wonderfully with the cats! I am great with children too! My foster parents say that I am required to go home to a house with a yard for me to run and play in! I would also LOVE to have another pup sibling to rough and tumble with! If you think thatI would be a good match for your family, send AZ Rez-cue an email so we can get together!

PLEASE INCLUDE: 
Tell us about your family! 
Do you have other animals at home? 
Do you rent or own your home? Does it have a fenced yard or park option? 
Have you owned animals in the past? If so, what kind? 
Do you have any questions for us? 

Emails that do not include this information will not be considered, as our adoption process required this knowledge to move forward! Thank you for your interest in one of our Rez-cues!

animal.description:
Tasha / Female / 1 Year / 35 lbs / Mountain Cur Mix / Toronto

Meet Tasha! Tasha comes to us al the way from Hohenwald, Tennessee! Tasha has been in foster care for a few weeks now, and continues to open up and come out of her shell. What her fosters have discovered so far is that she is sweet, playful, affectionate, timid and social. She loves to be part of the family and has nothing but potential ahead of her. When she’s not chewing on her bones or toys, she loves to play with other dogs! Tasha is now more than ready for a family of her own!

Tasha is cautious when meeting new people and may keep her distance. If people are calm generally it won’t take her long to come around for a sniff. Adopters should have realistic expectations when meeting her, as it will take time to earn her trust. Once you have built a bond with Tasha, you will have a friend for life!

Tasha is currently getting multiple walks a day, but still has accidents in the home. She will need support through potty training and be given time to adjust in a new environment. Outside she is fearful of loud or unexpected noises, so needs to be safely secured at all times. She may take a few minutes to gain the confidence to walk by something scary, but with gentle encouragement she is on her way. She is especially afraid of loud or large vehicles.

Tasha has not been left alone much in foster care, so it is unknown if she has any separation anxiety. If transitioning her to be alone for long periods, adopters should have a flexible schedule while she adjusts. Tasha will chew things around the house so she needs to be in a puppy proofed space for her safety. She also can jump high and will counter surf if given the chance!

She is very smart but has not mastered any commands yet. Once she is given time to decompress in her new home, she will benefit from ongoing obedience training. Still very much a puppy, she will need some encouragement for proper house manners and leash etiquette. Tasha loves to sniff so handlers should always have high value treats on hand to gain her focus!

Tasha would do best in a house, outside of the city. She is unsettled by the chaos city life so she will thrive in a suburban or country life. Tasha will need a fully fenced backyard to run, play and get out her zoomies! She loves the company of other dogs and all though not essential, would love another well adjusted dog in the home. Tasha would also do well with respectful children that are ages 10+.!

If you’re interested in adopting Tasha please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Tasha’s adoption fee is $800. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

animal.description: Lola is an incredibly sweet Lab/Pit mix. We've been fostering her since the puppies from her last (and final) litter were weaned and adopted and she has truly brightened our lives in the time she's been with us. My teens declared early on that "snuggle is Lola's love language and that pretty much says it all. Lola is masterful at getting as close to the people she loves as possible and showing you that you're the most important thing in her life. She is well-behaved and knows some basic commands, but she would benefit from some additional training, including leash training. Lola did fine with our existing dog, but my heart tells me that Lola would be happiest in a one-dog family. She has been fantastic with kids, although my only experience is with teenagers and dogs, and not little ones. I imagine she would be fine with children of all ages - she's got a very loving personality. The family or individual that ends up with Lola is going to be one very lucky family/person - we love her to death and while we'll hate to see her leave, we can't wait until her forever family finds her and gets to experience how amazing this sweet girl is.

Kasey is roughly around one to two years old. She is a sweet girl who is very active, smart, and would love to go on walks. We are currently working on house training and crate training. She is a playful girl who is looking for a family of her own and a home full of toys. Kasey does have a skin allergy and we give her an allergy shot every month.

Our adoption fee includes the spay/neuter, up to date vaccines, microchip, Interstate Health Certificate, and the transport service to get the new family pet to you. 

 Note: All dogs are located in foster homes in ALABAMA and will be transported NORTH AFTER ADOPTION. This means there is no way for a meet and greet before adoption. We try our best to give you honest personalities of the pup for you. We are more than happy to send videos, pictures, and even video chat so that you may have the connection with your pup before adoption. 

 All pets are delivered by a licensed transporter. 
The transportation company that we use is PETSLLC. They are well known and very professional. The link is listed, you are more than welcome to look and see what the closest drop off location is for you. 

http://www.petsllc.net/stops.php?route=9

 COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! If you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application!

 Please copy and paste the following URL for our adoption application:

 https://fs29.formsite.com/pickenscountypartnersforpets/form1/index.html

 Please be advised that our volunteers are busy rescuing, transporting, and caring for our animals. We will respond to your application as soon as possible. Upon review of your application, the rescue in Alabama will contact you, so you can ask any specific questions that you may have. 

 If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement.

 We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

animal.description:
Say hello to Oakley! This beautiful 11-month-old male husky is very playful, sweet, and affectionate. He is in need of a new loving home that can shower him with attention and exercise. 
He was surrendered to us due to eye problems that require medical treatment and result in eyesight issues. He moves around extremely well for his condition, it just takes him some time to adjust to his surroundings (he’s a pro at stairs now!) He does require a lot of exercise and stimulation and loves to go on runs/walks around the neighborhood. Oakley talks and sings to his family members and loves to cuddle. He really loves playing with his foster siblings and would do great in a home with other dogs. He does best with dogs his size or larger, so we are looking for a home with no cats or small dog breeds. ?Oakley struggles to spend time in his crate and has chewed through crates/destroyed crates to escape in the past. Fortunately, he does great being left around the house when left out. He is potty trained. He has been destructive to things before if they are left down in his reach but most of the time does well with enough exercise. 
His eyes are being managed by eye drops administered twice per day (morning & evening) but he will need continued care for his eye condition. Other than little bumps here and there around the house, you can hardly notice his eyesight issues. He’s happy and comfortable with life, just wants human and doggie playmates to enjoy it with.

animal.description:
Meet Gigi!  She is an amazing one year old, 60 pound dog that was hit by a car and miraculously survived.  She was seriously injured, though.  Gigi's pelvis was broken and one rear leg had been dislocated from its hip socket.  She had dozens of scrapes on her lower legs, too  The impact must have been enormous to cause so many skin tears and bone fractures.

Her former owner signed her over to animal control because they were not able to pay for her care.  We got Gigi  from animal control and she went directly to the vet clinic where she had orthopedic surgery the next day to repair both problems.  $4000 later, she is a happy girl and looking for her forever home.

Gigi is loving, house broken and can use a doggie door to let herself out.  She would love a doggie playmate and maybe some kids to love on her.  She still walks with a limp, but that will resolve with time as her muscles get built up again.  She is not in any pain, and loves to play with squeaky toys.  She especially likes the small ones that fit easily in her mouth.  Gigi is living with several other small dogs and gets along well with them.  She sleeps in her doggie bed every night.

Gigi has been spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for heartworms.  Her adoption fee is $300.00.

If you are interested in adopting this cutie, please write us at PricelessPoochRescue@gmail.com and ask for an application to adopt.  We are a foster-home based organization and Gigi is currently located in Hayesville, North Carolina, with frequent trips to the Atlanta area for adoptions.  The adoption process starts when you submit your application.  Once that has been approved, we will contact you to schedule a time for you to meet us.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Archer! I'm estimated to be a Cattle Dog mix born around 1/11/2018 . I came up to Wisconsin from Texas and weigh 50 pounds. I'm a shy dog that needs help in finding my confidence.  I enjoy other dogs and would do well with another dog in the home.  I'm gentle with people, just very unsure with life in general. If you have patience and time to let me adjust, you'll have changed my life completely around.  Apply for me today!

My adoption fee is $60.00. Adoption applications can be filled out at CCHS or online through our website, www.cchs-petshelter.org. Applications are not first come, first served. All applications will be reviewed by the adoption committee and the home chosen will be the one considered to be the best match. All dogs and puppies have been vaccinated for Distemper and Bordetella, dewormed and microchipped. If old enough, they will be vaccinated for Rabies and blood tested for Heartworm, Lymes, Anaplasmosis and Erlichiosis. Dogs and puppies will be spayed or neutered before adoption.

CCHS is proud to be a No-Kill Humane Society. As a private, non-profit charity, our work depends on donations and volunteers to keep going. We are committed to helping the animals that enter our doors and finding each the best possible forever home. CCHS has been inspected and licensed by the Department of Animal Health - DATCP. Our license is #268235-DS

animal.description:
Adoption Fee: $450
 Transport Fee: $160

Madison is roughly around a year old She is a sweet girl who is very active, smart, and would love to go on walks. We are currently working on house training and crate training. She is a playful girl who is looking for a family of her own and a home full of toys. 

Our adoption fee includes the spay/neuter, up to date vaccines, microchip, Interstate Health Certificate, and the transport service to get the new family pet to you. 

 Note: All dogs are located in foster homes in ALABAMA and will be transported NORTH AFTER ADOPTION. This means there is no way for a meet and greet before adoption. We try our best to give you honest personalities of the pup for you. We are more than happy to send videos, pictures, and even video chat so that you may have the connection with your pup before adoption. Please know we can only guess breed and age of our rescues.

 All pets are delivered by a licensed transporter. 
The transportation company that we use is PETSLLC. They are well known and very professional. The link is listed, you are more than welcome to look and see what the closest drop off location is for you. 

http://www.petsllc.net/stops.php?route=9

 COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! If you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application!

 Please copy and paste the following URL for our adoption application:

 https://fs29.formsite.com/pickenscountypartnersforpets/form1/index.html

 Please be advised that our volunteers are busy rescuing, transporting, and caring for our animals. We will respond to your application as soon as possible. Upon review of your application, the rescue in Alabama will contact you, so you can ask any specific questions that you may have. 

 If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement.

 We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

animal.description:
Meet Danny!

This adorable boy came to us from a neglect situation initially.  He was not abused, but the person who had him was physically unable to care for a puppy so family members stepped in and asked us to rehome him.  Danny is a typically sweet, playful puppy who just needs a forever family to love him.  He wants to play and snuggle in equal measure.  He will do best with a family who wants to play and interact with their puppy.  At this age he is probably a little overpowering for toddlers unless he is with a family that knows the Husky breed mix and can help toddlers through this stage.  Older children and all other people would be fine.  He is friendly and social.  He gets along well with dogs of all sizes.  We do not know how he would be with cats, but it is likely he’d want to play with them.

Danny is right at 4 months old and weighs about 20 lbs.  We expect he will be a medium sized adult dog (45-55 lbs ?) but could be wrong about that.  He is house trained to a doggy door.

If you think you might want to give this sweet pup a home, please email jojosdogrescue@gmail.com and we will send you an application, or visit our website: www.jojosdoghouse.com and download one.  Adoption fee is $250, which includes up-to-date vaccinations, parasite treatment, and microchip with lifetime registration.

Please visit our Facebook page JoJo's DogHouse (non-profit) to learn more about us and see many of the dogs we have rescued. We hope you'll join JoJo's family of adopters.

Our adoption fees vary and we are only able to accept payments by card* at this time but include spay/neuter, heartworm test (dogs), FeLV/FIV test (cats), age appropriate vaccines and deworming, flea, tick and heartworm medication and microchip.

animal.description:
Scooby is a very social, loving and handsome brindle boy looking for a family who has plenty of time to give him the exercise and attention that he needs.

He was house trained in his previous home and should do well in a new home if given time to adjust and a consistent routine.

He previously lived with kids of all ages, dog and cats.  He did well with all of them and would love to have companions in his new home!

Scooby is a typical hound who loves to use his nose to explore.  His nose tends to lead him astray thus he cannot be trusted off leash.  He would love to find a home with a fenced in yard where he can play freely and safely!  He would also make a great hiking partner!  Once he's tired out he is a wonderful snuggle buddy and will remind you to keep the pets coming by gently nudging you hand!

He is 1.5 years old and weighs 37.5 pounds.

***If you are interested in adopting please start by filling out an application available on our website and email it to us. https://www.couleehumane.com/adopt-an-animal

animal.description:
Rocky Road / Male / 10 Months / 40 lbs / Mountain Cur Mix / Oakville

Meet Rocky Road aka Rocky! Rocky comes to us all the way from Hohenwald, Tennessee! Rocky is described as affectionate, cuddly, loyal, playful and timid. He has been known to follow his fosters from room to room, gently licking their hands in hopes of getting a belly rub. He’s never met a squeaky toy he didn’t like, and his fosters discovered he has a particular affinity to a rubber fox. If you let him, Rocky can entertain himself all day with his toys. Rocky is looking for a patient and loving family to expose his full potential!

With people he hasn’t met before, he can be a little shy, but he is calm and keeps his distance. If given time to warm up, he will open up fairly quickly and be your new best friend. Rocky make take longer with some people, and new people should always be instructed to give him space. He hasn’t been tested with small children, but given his nature we predict he would do well children ages 10+, as long as they respect his space when needed.

As he has likely had little exposure to leashes, collars or harnesses, he is fearful of them. When he does get on leash, he freezes and it can take a few minutes to get him to leave the home. His forever family should be willing to desensitize him to his fears on leash, and build his confidence enough so he can enjoy walking with his people. While he adjusts, he will require a fully fenced back yard to drain physical and mental energy, along with enrichment games throughout the day. As he can be skittish with new people and loud noises, he should always be supervised in the backyard.

Still very much a puppy, Rocky's potty training is a work in progress. He wants to go outside, but he is still very fearful of the great outdoors. He will require a lot of patience, encouragement and consistency to build his confidence. His loving foster family has only had him for a few short weeks and they have already seen huge improvements. When he is left alone or at night, he is crated and settles quickly. If he is taken outside enough, Rocky has very few accidents.

Rocky is crated when left alone and hasn’t had any issues so far. If he’s has enough exercise for the day, he will sleep through the night! If left unsupervised, Rocky will chew things when he gets bored. He is a very good boy though, and usually just chews his toys.

Rocky's ideal family will have the time and resources to commit to his ongoing training, socialization and confidence building. He would prefer a home outside of the city or downtown core, and one with a fully fenced backyard. He has done well with dogs in the past, but he will resource guard toys if he doesn’t have enough structure. Potential adopters should have some experience managing this behavior and be able to redirect as needed. Rocky is only looking for cat-free homes.

If you are interested in adopting Rocky please fill out an application at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/dog-adoption/

Rocky’s adoption fee is $850. To learn more about our adoption fees and process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/faq/.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Name: Bear
Age: 15 years
Gender: Male
Breed: Lhasa Apso mix
Weight: 30 lbs
Dog friendly: TBD
Cat friendly: Unknown
Kid friendly: No
House Trained: Yes
Crate Trained: In progress
Energy level: Low
History: Owner surrender
Adoption Fee: $200

From the Foster:

If you're looking for a new companion who will add some serious cuteness to your life, Bear may be for you! Bear is an incredibly sweet, kind, old soul. He is a go-with-the-flow guy; ready with a wagging tail for a walk at a moment's notice, but also totally fine lounging the day away!

The main things to know about Bear: he's friendly to the people he has met, agreeable on walks with other dogs and people around. He is house trained, but not sure how well he will adapt to a crate - he certainly has made his distaste known when inside it! Bear's current house does not have other dogs, cats, or kiddos, so not sure how he would adapt to them. His current fosters think he was previously the only dog in the house, but would probably be okay with a buddy! Bear is welcoming to visitors - previous owners reported some aggression with young kids, but he likely would do alright with school aged or older kids in the house. He has been a total happy camper with adults. He is a curious one on walks; he does very well on a leash, but also likes to take it fairly slow.

While he is not a beagle like Snoopy, he has some "Joe Cool" energy. He enjoys human company as well as plenty of naps - he would be flexible, and likely adapt well to a variety of households. He has no notable arthritis, although would prefer to limit stair climbing in general. He takes a daily liver supplement (with no issues, all you need is a bit of peanut butter!) and would need lab monitoring every 6 months. While he's not a big cuddler, he's the type of companion who always wants to be near his humans. He doesn't require much socialization or mental stimulation and would LOVE for his next home to be the perfect place to live out his golden years.

animal.description:
The name Paloma means beautiful and this gal is just that and more. Just look at this unique black and grey coat. And her eyes! Hello? They are mesmerizing! A tranquil blue/grey. Ok, enough about the obvious. Deep down, all Paloma really wants out of life is a young and or active family or couple to take her on jaunts on a hiking trail or a run on the beach. A big backyard? Yes, please. A dog park? Let's go! She's a youngster, around 1-2 years old, full of life, and ready to please. She weighs about 36 pounds. She gets on well with her buds at the farm and is always on the go, go, go! Super curious and wants to meet and greet everyone! She sleeps awesome in her crate and is potty trained. She also does very well walking on a leash. This beautiful girl is anxious to meet you, too!

Please note we are working with limited staff/volunteers at this time. For full details of our current adoption appointment policy, please see https://savinggracenc.org/adoption-appointments-during-this-time/. Highlights:

We are working with a very limited staff/volunteer base

We do not have the people power to respond to emails/call about specific dogs

Our appointments are limited to 2 people at a time and for a maximum of 30 minutes.

Please arrive at your appointment ready to meet the dogs we have available. At this time, many dogs are in foster families or not yet posted on our website. Be flexible and ready to meet any number of wonderful dogs available onsite at the time of your appointment.

All puppies and dogs at Saving Grace are crate trained, have been spayed/neutered, are up to date on their vaccinations, are on heartworm preventative and have been microchipped. Their adoption fee is $375.00. Each has been carefully screened for disposition and temperament in order to provide your home with a safe companion that will enjoy life as your new family member.

Our Adoption Form can be completed online at our website at https://savinggracenc.org/how-to-adopt/ .

An Adoption Form is required before setting up an appointment to meet with a potential adoptee or a foster home.

Sending an Adoption Form does not commit you to an adoption, it simply provides us with background information on potential homes.

If you'd like to donate to help cover the cost of care for these wonderful dogs awaiting new homes, please visit the donate page on our website at https://savinggracenc.org/donate-now/ .

Saving Grace is a small, non-profit 501-C3 organization operated by volunteers only. Most of our animals come from rural animal control shelters where lack of space and resources limit their time and adoption possibilities. Thank you for choosing Saving Grace! We look forward to helping you find your new companion and family member.

animal.description:
Penelope (AKA Penny) is a healthy 3-year-old female who is housebroken, spayed, and up-to-date on all her shots. Her days are very structured and she is doing very well with her foster family, but she is looking for a forever home! She is learning basic commands and needs someone who will continue with her  training. Her foster dad’s dedication and patience have allowed her to come out of her shell and now her true personality shines through!

Penny has been in a foster home since early January. She is currently living with 4 adults and one 8-year-old child in the home, as well as 2 parakeets. Although she’s loving and friendly with everyone in the household and everyone she meets, at this time we feel that a home without small children or small animals would be best so that she can continue to blossom the way she has been over the last several weeks. She’ll do well with an active family, but does best in a calm home environment. Meet and greets are required for any potential fur siblings. She does well in the car and walks nice on lead. Penny does well being left alone at home and is currently in the process of being crate trained.

From her foster dad:
“I would describe her as medium energy. She loves chilling on the couch as much as exploring new places. She’s young and athletic and perfectly capable of keeping up with outdoor adventures. She’ll ramp up her energy to match yours. At the same time, after long activity periods, she’ll sleep soundly on the couch or bed or wherever. And she loves cuddles. Often peaking with one eye to make sure you’re still there.”

Penny is a bouncy, affectionate, and playful sweetheart. We know her forever family is out there and whoever is lucky enough to adopt Penny will have a best friend for life!

APPLY TO ADOPT PENNY:
www.oatsandgoatsrescue.com/adopt

Follow Her Adventures with her Foster Dad:
www.m.Facebook.com/PittiePenelope

Follow Our Facebook Page for More Updates and Videos:
https://www.facebook.com/oatsandgoatsrescue/

animal.description:
Chance is a very special and handsome Texas Blue Heeler puppy that is needing a home that understands his breed and his quiet shyness. This puppy has been through so much at a young age and is what you would call a SURVIVOR! He is such a sweet, special boy who needs just the right family for his forever home. When Chance first came into foster care, he was so scared of new people and surroundings that he hid behind the couch and refused to come out. He wouldn't walk on a leash, and he cowered and ran when someone approached him. A few weeks later, he has come such a long way!! He loves to snuggle in bed and get belly rubs, enjoys car rides to and from school every day, and looks forward to his daily walks around the neighborhood with his buddy Rocky (a 2 year old Golden retriever). He is still scared of new people though. When kids in the neighborhood come out to pet Rocky, Chance hides behind his foster mom and doesn't want to be touched. He is quite territorial also and gives delivery men more than a friendly bark when they step on our porch. Chance is scared of loud noises along with unfamiliar people, and he startles very easily. He needs a quiet home environment with a family who will be patient and understanding with him as he takes the time he needs to adjust to his new life. Once he feels safe and loved, Chance will bond very strongly with the person or people that belong to him. Then he won't be able to give or get enough love. He'll follow you from room to room, sit in your lap for love, and will always want to be close to your side. A home without young children will be best for him since he does prefer predictable behavior from his humans. He currently lives with cats and can't resist chasing them for fun but doesn't exhibit any aggression toward them at all. He would do very well in a home with another dog. He has bonded with Rocky and definitely has more confidence and less fear when the two of them are together. He is nervous and hesitant to walk on a leash alone but trots along by Rocky's side wherever he goes. The two of them also enjoy daily "tough puppy" play. They enjoy wrestling and chasing each other around the yard.. and swiping each other's toys and chew bones when they get a good opportunity. Ideally Chance would like a fenced in yard and/or several acres of land to call his own. Such a wonderful handsome boy for just the right family with the experience, love, and understanding he needs to grow and thrive. This boy is not Mr. Congeniality. He is a smart, devoted but damaged early in his life Blue Heeler that just needs a quiet and non-busy home.

Please email us at ccrtennessee@gmail.com

ADOPTION FEE REQUIRED. Contact ccrtennessee@gmail.com.

animal.description:
****Please DO NOT message the rescue asking if this puppy is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. The first step in our adoption process is to fill out an adoption application at www.snarrnortheast.org. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO & FAQs BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: Topaz
*Age: 4 months
*Current Weight: 15 pounds
*Rescued from: Texas
*Adoption fee: $495 (plus $125 spay/neuter deposit, which is refundable when spay/neuter agreement is fulfilled)
*Health: up to date on puppy shots so far (adopter will be responsible for remaining puppy vaccinations)

Topaz and her littermates are arriving in New York soon and ready to meet their amazing new families and enjoy a whole new life.  They are an active bunch and love wrestling with each other.  Their mom is a small breed terrier mix around 25 pounds, we think the dad is a neighbor's dog  that's medium size probably a Australian shepherd/lab mix.  Another friendly dog in the house would be great for these cuties, an older playful canine sibling can teach them house manners and show them how to live the good life.  These puppies may be a little timid at first, when separated from their littermates, but we are sure that won't last long.  We can't wait for these guys to learn all about snow.  If you are looking for a pretty girl with energy and puppy kisses to give, maybe Topaz is the pup for you.

This litter of adorable puppies was rescued from an area where there is an abundance of homeless dogs, and not a lot of shelter space for them to go while they wait for their forever homes. They will be arriving at SNARR's Adoption Center in Brewster, NY on February 17 ready for adoption! 

IMPORTANT: This puppy has not yet been altered. For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a strictly-enforced signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

To apply to adopt a puppy from this litter, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications.  

**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**
We do recommend listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice when applying for puppies with several littermates.
(Littermates: )

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
Ooooh, look at this handsome boy! Say hello to Leo! <3

"Leo is just about perfect. He has adjusted to indoor life so quickly. He learned he liked comfy beds on the first day. He has learned toys are so fun and he likes to have a lot of them around him. He is a mixture of gentle, loving, playful. He likes to be with his people but is also confident enough to take a quiet nap alone. He loves food and is quite the table surfer but we are working on that one tiny flaw. The foster puppies are teaching him how to play with others and he is quickly catching on. This gentle soul will steal your heart quickly, he did ours!"

Leo came to us after he went after his owner's poultry. He was a bit too playful to handle a guardian role with them. His owners wanted to make sure he ended up somewhere safe and surrendered him to us. Leo is a 6-month-old male Great Pyrenees/Border Collie mix. He currently weighs about 40lbs. Leo does great when meeting new people. He is a happy, tail wagging goofball but doesn't jump up on people. He would do well in public settings, and would probably try to befriend everyone around! Leo has not shown to have any food aggression or issues with resource guarding in his foster home. He also doesn't jump on people. Leo is initially anxious in the car but settles down quickly. Leo is working on his leash training but is scared on the leash. We do believe that Leo would be a good candidate for apartment living. 


Leo is a mix of calm and playful. Leo is unfamiliar with playing fetch. We are unsure if he is a water dog or not. Leo does LOVE his toys! Leo has not shown to be a big barker in his foster home. When no one is home, Leo has free-run of the house. At night, Leo sleeps on his fosters bed, couch, or doggie bed. Leo is potty trained, but his foster has not needed to kennel him. 

With his looks and awesome personality, Leo will be the perfect addition to any family! <3 Before you get that app in for him, here are a few additional things to note

-Leo is initially shy of the other dogs. Once he warms up to them he becomes more playful with them. 

-Leo is good with cats. 

-Leo is good with kids of all ages. He is gentle with them and doesn't jump. 

-Leo is still young so his new family should have their house puppy-proofed. So far, Leo has mainly chewed on his toys. Being a pup, he may steal a shoe that is left out, though ;) 

Leo would be perfect in any home. He just wants to be with his people. He is a mixture of calm, quiet, loving, and learning how to play. He is very gentle with the puppies, dogs, and cats in the house. He loves to snuggle on the couch or in bed with the kids. He is still learning what a leash does but we believe once he learns it’s ok he will be a perfect companion for any adventure. If you want to find your best friend in Leo, apply to adopt him at https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app

His adoption fee is $225. That includes DHLPP, Rabies, and Bordatella shots. She will be micro-chipped, heart-worm tested, have a fecal done, be de-wormed, be spayed/neutered, and will be current on heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

animal.description:
Hope was brought into a high kill shelter in Texas as a stray, and unfortunately she was a familiar face to the staff. Hope was brought in on SEVERAL occasions but always reclaimed by her “owner”. We say owner very lightly, how could anyone treat their animal this way, let them suffer in this way, and who in their right mind would give a dog in this condition back to the person who “owned” them. Those scars weren’t all new. Every time Hope was brought into to the shelter she was in this type of horrific condition. Hope was likely running from her abusers trying to escape the life of hell in wich she lived in, only to be caught and brought to a shelter where she had little chance of making it out alive and if she did it was only to be reclaimed and sent back to her life of torture. (After receiving her records we saw documentation of times she was brought to the shelter dating all the way back to 2016!!!!) 

Hopes photos were posted by a volunteer begging for someone to save her. We saw her, all of her, the scars that covered her body, the crooked jaw, the weepy oozing eyes, the deep open wounds, but what we also saw was her beautiful colors, her contagious smile, her hopeful eyes and her fight to live! Hope was still on her stray hold and we were told her owner would likely come back to reclaim her. We were terrified. Terrified that that monster would come back for her, or what was left of her. For two days we waited in un explainable worry....but thankfully he never showed! As soon as that stray hold was up our volunteers went and freed her. 

This is also how we found Sugar Ray, sweet sweet Sugar Ray. (Click here to read his story - https://www.facebook.com/177799072926038/posts/523656111673664/?d=n) The same volunteer who posted about Hope told us about sugar Ray and begged us to save him too. When she showed us his face we couldn’t say no, Hope lead us to Sugar Ray and Hope will forever carry a part of Sugar Ray with her. 

Hope was seen by our texas veterinarians immediately. They checked all of her wounds, took x rays of her jaw, completed all tests and provided a treatment plan to get this sweet girl healthy! After 6 months of Heartworm treatment, and another 5 months of routine vet care including surgery on her jaw (the excess skin hanging from prior injury) she is finally ready to head to maine to find her furever home! 

HOPE IS

Approximately 4 years old 
English bulldog mix 
Spayed
Microchipped 
Up to date on vaccines 
Negative for Heartworm & tick borne diseases
Very friendly and boisterous
Has done well with male dogs but should be the only dog in the home

animal.description:
For my Petfinder.com friends, please contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information. My ID number is 336914

I am available for adoption; however due to my breed my adoption will have to be facilitated with a rescue organization. Please see the front desk staff or contact the Shelter at (248) 858-1070 for more information.

Meet Princess Starlight! While this little one is quite shy at the Shelter, once she is in a loving home, and comfortable, she will come out of her shell, revealing her very sweet nature and fun personality! Princess came from a home that she shared with several other dogs, and didn't seem to mind having a group of friends around. At such a young age, this pretty lady, has incredible potential to learn and grow into a successful new friend!

American Pit Bulls are a misunderstood breed; for this reason, we implore adopters to these beautiful dogs to be very vigilant in training and socialization. This breed is very energetic and will need daily exercise. Because of their strength and energy, apartment living may not be the best fit. This breed can be loving, loyal and very smart. 

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption. 

 Primary Color: Black Secondary Color: White Weight: 34lbs Age: 1yrs 0mths 2wks Animal has been Spayed

animal.description:
Adoption Fee: $450
 Transport Fee: $160

Kona is roughly around a year old . She is a sweet girl who is very active, smart, and is a little shy.We are currently working on house training and crate training. She is a playful girl once you gain her trust, she needs someone that is willing to spend time with her and gain her trust she is looking for a family of her own and a home full of toys. 

Our adoption fee includes the spay/neuter, up to date vaccines, microchip, Interstate Health Certificate, and the transport service to get the new family pet to you. 

 Note: All dogs are located in foster homes in ALABAMA and will be transported NORTH AFTER ADOPTION. This means there is no way for a meet and greet before adoption. We try our best to give you honest personalities of the pup for you. We are more than happy to send videos, pictures, and even video chat so that you may have the connection with your pup before adoption. Please know we can only guess breed and age of our rescues.

 All pets are delivered by a licensed transporter. 
The transportation company that we use is PETSLLC. They are well known and very professional. The link is listed, you are more than welcome to look and see what the closest drop off location is for you. 

http://www.petsllc.net/stops.php?route=9

 COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! If you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application!

 Please copy and paste the following URL for our adoption application:

 https://fs29.formsite.com/pickenscountypartnersforpets/form1/index.html

 Please be advised that our volunteers are busy rescuing, transporting, and caring for our animals. We will respond to your application as soon as possible. Upon review of your application, the rescue in Alabama will contact you, so you can ask any specific questions that you may have. 

 If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement.

 We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21.

He already knows sit, and it's a surefire bet, that if he doesn't know more, he'll learn quicker than a second. If you're looking for a dog who'll ease in and become a part of your family, then Suba is your guy!

animal.description:
****Please DO NOT message the rescue asking if this puppy is still available; if a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. The first step in our adoption process is to fill out an adoption application at www.snarrnortheast.org. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO & FAQs BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: Toto
*Age: 4 months
*Current Weight: 15 pounds
*Rescued from: Texas
*Adoption fee: $495 (plus $125 spay/neuter deposit, which is refundable when spay/neuter agreement is fulfilled)
*Health: up to date on puppy shots so far (adopter will be responsible for remaining puppy vaccinations)

Toto and his littermates are arriving in New York soon and ready to meet their amazing new families and enjoy a whole new life.  They are an active bunch and love wrestling with each other.   Their mom is a small breed terrier mix around 25 pounds, we think the dad is a neighbor's dog  that's medium size probably a Australian shepherd/lab mix.  Another friendly dog in the house would be great for these cuties, an older playful canine sibling can teach them house manners and show them how to live the good life.  These puppies may be a little timid at first, when separated from their littermates, but we are sure that won't last long.  We can't wait for these guys to learn all about snow.  If you are looking for a handsome boy with energy and puppy kisses to give, maybe Toto is the pup for you.

This litter of adorable puppies was rescued from an area where there is an abundance of homeless dogs, and not a lot of shelter space for them to go while they wait for their forever homes. They will be arriving at SNARR's Adoption Center in Brewster, NY on January 17th ready for adoption! 

IMPORTANT: This puppy has not yet been altered. For any dog or puppy that is not able to be spayed/neutered prior to adoption, SNARR requires a $125 deposit in addition to your adoption fee, as well as a strictly-enforced signed Spay/Neuter Contract stating you will have this dog altered within 6 months of adoption. The $125 deposit will be returned once the contract has been fulfilled. 

To apply to adopt a puppy from this litter, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications.  

**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**
We do recommend listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice when applying for puppies with several littermates.
(Littermates: )

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
Porthos / Male / 5 years / 60 lbs / Catahoula Leopard Dog / Toronto

Meet Porthos! Porthos comes to us all the way from Hohenwald, Tennessee! This handsome and gentle giant is not interested in toys or treats, just human affection. His fosters describe him as the “ultimate snuggle buddy.” Wherever his person goes - he is sure to be close behind and curious about what they’re doing. He is described as shy, sweet, easy going, loyal, calm, curious and loving. He loves being with other dogs, going for walks, and exploring the outside. He would make the ultimate companion for an active family who shares his love of the outdoors!

Porthos is the ultimate gentleman and never jumps up on anyone. He is very excited when his family comes home but is always calm and respectful. With new people he will go in for a sniff, and generally warms up quickly. Your typical Catahoula, he is cautious of new people but wants to trust. Based on his nature, he would make an incredible dog to grow up with respectful children of all ages. It may take him a few days to adjust to the energy of children, but Porthos doesn’t have a bad bone in his body.

Porthos is currently getting 4 long walks a day. He is a working breed so he will need structured walks throughout the day to ensure he is successful. As long as he’s had enough exercise, he is extremely well mannered in the home. Porthos would also benefit from daily mental enrichment and structured outdoor activities!

Porthos hasn’t been left alone much in foster care, as he always prefers to be with his humans. So far he doesn’t like his crate unless it’s on his terms. He would prefer a home with at least one family member who is home more often than not. The one time he was left completely alone he destroyed his doggie tote out of anxiety. Transitioning him to a regular work day will take time and patience! Adopters should have a flexible schedule and some knowledge on separation anxiety to support him through it. Porthos prefers to sleep close to his humans on a doggy bed.

On leash Porthos is a puller. He is a powerful dog so he should never be walked by children, only strong handlers. His leash etiquette should be a primary focus for his training moving forward. He is quite skittish outside and will jump or startle easily to loud noises. He will also need support with basic obedience and commands.

Porthos’ ideal home would be a detached house, with a fully fenced backyard. He is used to wide open spaces to run and play, so would do best with a safely secured place to enjoy the outdoors. Porthos is only looking for homes outside of the city, where he can really start to thrive. Porthos craves the company of other dogs, so is looking for homes with at least one other well balanced dog in the home.

If you are interested in adopting Porthos please fill out an application at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/dog-adoption/

Porthos’ adoption fee is $800. To learn more about our adoption fees and process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/faq/.

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to htar.lauren@gmail.com.

Due to COVID-19 precautions, all animals for adoption through Homeward Trails can be met by appointment only. You can make an appointment to meet available dogs at our ADOPTION CENTER by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet and available cats at MEOW PALACE by going to https://www.signupgenius.com/go/20f084ea8ae2da5f49-meet1. 
For animals in FOSTER homes, please submit an online application and an adoption team will reply with next steps. We thank you for your patience as we work to keep saving lives during this difficult time. 

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE: http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Adoption Coordinator: Lauren T
Location: Foster

This sweet momma is Annie. Annie came to us just having given birth to 8 puppies! She is a very sweet and loving girl who deserves to be taken care of as well as she has her pups!

Annie is well housebroken and has medium energy, but it is hard to tell if that is her normal energy level, or if she is still resting up after taking such good care of her puppies. She's an incredibly sweet girl, but is startled by men. She will warm up to her current foster dad, but barks when she sees him in a new room. She has not exhibited aggression, but if there is a man in her household he will need to be patient with her to allow her time to trust him. 

She is treat motivated and sleeps well throughout the night on her dog bed! 

She will get a little anxious when left (paces, looking through the house for someone) but will settle down after a little while. She will do great with someone who can help her learn that its ok being left alone and that her person will always come back! 

She knows basic commands like paw, sit, and down. She's a very smart girl. 

The adoption fee for this dog/puppy is $475. This fee includes spay/neuter and microchip. 

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

 We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program

animal.description:
Elvis 
2 year old Male Tree Walker Coon Hound. 

He is a sweet sweet boy. Very much a hound and loves to use his nose. Has had some previous training as he does know sit, stay, down. He was locked in a shelter for 7 months and found his way on the euthanasia list! We couldn’t let that happen! 
So he made his journey to Illinois where he waits to find his forever home. He is slow to warm up and will need to be given space. He has shown resource guarding with food, toys, and blankets in new situations. He very much needs a place to feel safe and once he does those quirks have gone away. 
He is 47.5 lbs and full grown. Potty trained and non destructive. He is not a dog that can be kenneled for he has a fear of them from being locked in one for 7 months! He has proven to be good with other animals but a meet and greet is mandatory. He warms up quicker to females and takes a little longer to warm up to men.

Mae is a dreamy giant that will steal your heart! She is a Great Pyrenees and we highly recommend researching the breed before jumping in to get one. They are very striking dogs, noble, and kind to those they know. They prefer a home with land where they can roam and oversee their domain, however they shouldn't be left to free roam without a fence to keep them on the property. Livestock guardian breeds have a very large roaming range that often expands further than most single farm properties. Many GPs are indifferent to other dogs off their property. Mae is tolerant of other dogs. She prefers to have the companionship of people. She leans in and nudges for more petting, and would love nothing more than to find a family to cuddle her. 

Mae was found stray in rural Ohio. She is undergoing treatment for tick-born illnesses and an ear infection that will most likely require surgery. Gigi's will cover the cost of the surgery and follow-up care. Follow-up care post surgery is very minimal, and she should be healed within 2-3 weeks after surgery. Mae is being offered as Foster-to-Adopt through her treatment and will be available for the foster family to adopt once she's cleared medically. She will also be spayed and receive a dental before being adopted. Mae is currently 83 pounds and approximately 3 years old.

For additional information about her medical status or inquiry about foster-to-adopting her, please email us: adopt@gigis.org

animal.description:
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?

animal.description:
Foster location:  Boise ID
Breed:  Husky Mix
Age:  2 years old
Adoption Fee:  $200.00
Spayed, Vaccinated, Microchipped

If interested you MUST complete the Adoption Application:  http://fuzzypawzrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application-2/



Juno is a husky mix who came to Fuzzy Pawz Rescue through no fault of her own. She is just an all-around nice dog who would do well with most active families.  

This pretty girl is so sweet and loves her people, whether it is cuddle time, play time or time for a run she’s into it with you.  But as with all Husky’s she can get into trouble if she is bored.  Keep her exercised every day and she will be the best companion ever!

Juno does great with other dogs when given a proper introduction. She loves to play and would love a home with another playful dog. Her foster sisters are smaller than she is and she plays very appropriately. She can be intimidating to new dogs at first, so she should always be supervised with introductions. But she is actually on the submissive side and not aggressive at all when playing.

She needs some leash work, but will calm down once all the wiggles are out. She’d do best in an active home with daily walks or other forms of exercise. We are told her favorite thing is to go on bike rides and run beside the bike. We have not had the opportunity to do that in her foster home. But exercise is especially important for her as she does have a bit of separation anxiety that can be helped with physical and mental activities.

Juno is also kid and cat friendly. Because of her size though, she should go to a home with children over 8. She would not do well in a home where her family leaves her frequently for weekends away from home and activities. She wants nothing more than to hang with both her foster parents in a situation where she is comfortable. She’s just a really great dog with nice manners and wants to please her people.

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.If interested in adopting an available dog read about our Adoption Process and then complete an Adoption Application. Both can be found under the Adopt menu item on the website. A veterinarian evaluates all dogs taken in by Mo-Kan Border Collie Rescue . All required shots are administered; checked for intestinal parasites; heart worms and they are spayed/neutered.

Dogs on the Sponsorship page may or may not be available for adoption yet, but can be Sponsored. Read more under the We Need You menu item on the website.

Courtesy Listings have not been evaluated by MoKanBCR. Please refer to the contact info in the bio.
Marshall is a 2 year old male smooth coat border collie looking for his forever home. Marshall is a snuggler and loves attention. He likes to go on hikes and play in the yard but he is also content to sit with the family on the couch to watch TV. He is great with other dogs. He solicits play well and can also take a hint if the other dog is not feeling equally playful. Good with both big dogs and little dogs, he likes to be near them but is respectful of their space.

Marshall is house trained but does need to be let out frequently. He is currently crated while we are at work and left to roam the house overnight with the other dogs. He has not gotten into anything or chewed anything up. After being crated for several hours he can be rambunctious when he is let out again but taking him out to the yard to play right after seems to do the trick. He usually settles pretty quickly.

Marshall is great with kids, he usually chooses to sleep in my children's bed at night (our bed is taken up by a very moody Frenchie). He is very good about leaving all their toys alone (their rooms are extremely messy). He would do best with children who are 6+ years old as he does sometimes put his paws up on them and could potentially knock over really little ones.

He does try to put his paws on people when he greets them but we are working to curb this behavior, he's doing well but does forget sometimes. He walks fairly well on the leash but will pull (also a behavior we are working on). I have not seen any leash reactivity towards people or other dogs. He has gone on several dog play dates and has done very well. He is bright and very food motivated.

Marshall is a great dog! A pleasure to have in the house and so much fun. See the video of his great play behaviors, how he interacts with other dogs and our guests who he met for the first time that day, you can also see he is very athletic and he bounds around the yard. He's beautiful!

Marshall is being fostered in the St. Louis, MO area.Click here to watch a video of Marshall.

Mya is an 8 month old spayed female German Shepherd.

animal.description:
Meet Clifford! This dog has the most beautiful eyes and a heart of pure gold! He is a terrier mix with beautiful brindle coloring and he weighs about 15 pounds. He is 2 to 3 years old. We found Clifford laying on the floor of a kill shelter near the Mexico border. He was crippled and could not walk so we rescued him and took him to our vet. We discovered that Clifford had two broken legs on opposite sides of his body. His x-rays were sent to a specialist who is an expert in plate repairs and he agreed that he could help Clifford. He has had his surgery and as you can see in the video, doing remarkably well! He will be released for full activity on Feb 8th and we can't wait to see him running full speed through the yard. He is friendly, and has been the perfect houseguest in his foster home. Clifford loves everyone so would make a great addition to any family. We are looking for the perfect home for this most perfect little dog. He is SO special!

For more on Cliffords story, please view our Facebook page. https://www.facebook.com/TracysPawsRescue


Clifford is located in a wonderful foster home in San Antonio. We will arrange a time to meet Clifford once your application to adopt him has been approved. He is neutered, up to date on all shots, microchipped and his adoption fee is $300. If you would like to add Clifford to your family, please complete an application here-

https://www.tracyspawsrescue.org/adoption-application

Services our dogs receive prior to adoption:
Chagas Testing
Heartworm Testing (age appropriate)
Tick Illness Testing (age appropriate)
All age appropriate vaccines
Heartworm and flea/tick preventatives
Spay/neuter surgery
Microchip

animal.description:
Pumpkin Spice is Ready for Adoption. 

We welcomed Pumpkin back in October. We were surprised when she arrived pregnant. On November 15th she gave birth to 5 beautiful puppies. On Jan 19th she was spayed. After weeks of healing we are ready to begin her heartworm treatment protocol. Which is a month of antibiotics and then 3 vet visits which are one injection One month. If you are local we have to have you use our vet for us to cover treatment 100%. 
Pumpkin is about 1 1/2yr old, 25lbs and fully grown. Pumpkin Spice loves to cuddle all the time, has high toy drive loves to play & fetch. She is completely house broken. We have learned to sit and stay, she loves to learn each day. She's a doll on a leash. 
There is not a mean bone in her body. She plays with our 5lb chiweenie to 40lb dogs in our home. Cats are up in air, she does love barking at them through fence. 
Pumpkin is a puppy without all the hassles. Can be home for up to 8hrs, but would rather home bodies.
Application are @ Www.thewoofpack007tinyanimalrescue.org

animal.description: Meet Gretel! She's a super pretty 2 and a half year old Australian Cattle Dog/Blue Heeler, Though timid by nature, Gretel's foster family reports that she is sweet and cuddly once she's gotten to know you. She also really LOVES being around other dogs, but she hasn't met any cats yet. Gretel's ideal home would have a big backyard where she can roll in the grass and chase squirrels - she is very fast! Being so treat motivated and smart, Gretel has gotten really good at house manners and staying in her crate. We think she will do best in a more quiet home where she can really get comfortable with her people. Would you like to set-up a meeting with Gretel? Contact ARF, and we'll make it happen!

animal.description:
This petite Princess is looking for a castle to call her own! She came to us at the shelter when her previous owner could no longer care for her, so Princess is on the hunt for a new kingdom to rule! Princess has lived with other small dogs in the past, as well as woman and children, but men can sometimes make her a little nervous and she likes to take her time getting to know them. Like all royalty, she has certain likes and dislikes when it comes to sharing her toys and treats -- but more than anything, this little lady wants a forever family and a home to call her own!

Thank you for your interest in our adoptable animals! Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, we do require appointments to see our adoptable animals. Please complete the adoption application and a Customer Care Associate will be in contact with you. PLEASE NOTE: We ask that when you submit your application, that you are available to schedule an appointment within the next 24-48 hours.

animal.description:
Hello! Wondering how old I am? Well, that’s a secret only I’m willing to tell! I’ve heard a few guesses but all you need to know is I may be an older boy but I can still run around when I want to! I’m not a big fan of harnesses and leashes but I’m starting to get the hang of it. See now, you can teach an old dog new tricks! My new family will need to be patient with me. I’m the sweetest boy full of lots of love and tail wags but I need to get to know you first. I love it when people sit and talk to me and I love going outside to a yard where I don’t need that pesky harness. 
*Might do ok with a smaller, calm dog
*Might do ok with cats if they are dog savvy. May chase.

animal.special_needs_notes:
I have arthritis, I’m sure I don’t need to tell you, but it’s one of the joys of getting older. But don’t worry, I have some medication that makes me feel good as new! I’m sorry but I do need a quiet home without lots of stairs so no apartments for me. I will need medications going forward to help keep my joints comfortable so expect some additional costs with medications. Trust me though, when you see my dazzling smile and fluffy tail wag and come running towards you, you’ll forget all about my small flaws. 
*no kids
*no apartments

animal.description: Our boy Coal has been a wonderful and rewarding project for his foster. He came to her hiding and terrified. He now LOVES to play with his foster siblings and they have really given him confidence! He definitely needs a home with other dogs! Cola is approx 1 year old and about 45lbs. This boy will continue to be a project with gaining confidence. A quieter household will be best but the sky is the limit with how far he has come in just 2 weeks! He is fully vetted, house trained, crate trained and ready to roll. Please be prepared to continue his confidence building and leash work as he is still pretty scared away from home. This boy is going to be such a rewarding adoption. If you are interested in sweet Coal please fill out the application on our website finalvictoryrescue.com and if approved we will schedule a virtual meet and greet!

animal.description:
Big King came to us in September when a good Samaritan saw him get pushed out of a car. When King first arrived he was stressed and was looking for someone he could trust. King was looking for his knights in shining armor to show him the way. King found his knights and many royal subjects here at Lollypop Farm. King's knights went on many quests to prove to the king that there was compassion in the world, and that the world is not a scary place after all. King started to understand what his knight's and royal subject's were showing him. Thus he started to go on grand adventures. His favorite adventure is going on long hikes through the enchanted woods. 

Alas the time has come for the King to find his castle and his one true knight. King is looking for a calm and quiet castle. He is looking for an adult only castle with no other pets. If you think you might be the knight for King please reach out to nlapresi@lollypop.org for more information.

animal.description:
Susie is a 25 pound, 3 year old beagle that was surrendered with her sister Sunshine when they both flunked out of rabbit hunting school. While she is not going to give Elmer Fudd a run for his money, she most certainly could find a chicken nugget hidden in the house in 15 seconds flat! Susie walks nicely on the leash, and she is working on her potty training. She doesn’t mind being crated and she is SUPER food motivated but doesn’t have any food guarding issues. She will need regular exercise and to have her food intake carefully monitored because she would gladly eat her weight in dog food three times over daily. She really enjoys the company of other playful dogs so she would be happiest in a home with another dog (like her sister Sunshine). As is typical for a beagle, she will also follow an interesting scent anywhere so she will need a fenced yard or to remain on leash to keep her from  following her little nose off into far away places.

This dog is spayed, up to date on vaccinations and current on flea/tick and heartworm preventative.  This dog has tested negative  for heartworms.  The adoption fee is $450 if your adoption is prepaid and final prior to your dog's arrival. An additional $50 will be charged on dogs that are picked up from our Southbury CT adoption center, adopted at an event or foster home. This additional fee is necessary in order to comply with CT HB 5368.
If you are a MA resident, your new family member is required to go through a mandatory 48 hour quarantine period at our Woburn MA isolation facility.  Your new family member will be dropped off by our transport on Thursday and will be ready for you to pick him/her up on Saturday between 12pm-2pm.  An additional $100 fee will be added for any dogs picked up from the Woburn MA quarantine facility.  This additional fee is necessary in order to comply with MA Order 405-CD-12 and Order 1-AHO-05. 

TO APPLY PLEASE GO TO  www.cprdogs.com.  If your application was successfully submitted you will get a confirmation.  
After receipt of your application, an adoption counselor will then be in touch to answer your questions about this pup, discuss the adoption process and get the ball rolling!  If you have not heard from one of our volunteers within 5 days of submitting your application, please email mollibo@gmail.com.

animal.description:
Chili is not at Westport Animal Control.  He is a WASA foster.  For additional information about him, please contact WASA by calling 203 557 0361 or by sending an email to wasa1@optonline.net.  WASA has a limited adoption area.  

Chili is an adorable and sweet senior (approximately 12) Merle Pomeranian.  He has been brought up to date on his vet care and is doing marvelously in is foster home.  We are looking for a relatively quiet home with an individual or family that have the time and resources to provide him with a wonderful life.  We would prefer a home where he is the only dog in residence but will consider a home where there is another small, chill senior dog (like the one currently residing in his foster home).  

To complete an online application (necessary prior to a meet and greet), please visit:  http://www.westportwasa.org/adopt/wasa-adoption-application/

** COVID-19 UPDATES ARE AVAILABLE ON OUR WEBSITE AT https://westvalleyhumanesociety.org/COVID/ **

All dogs adopted from West Valley Humane Society are up to date on vaccines, microchipped, parasite treated and spayed/neutered.  Please note that we do not respond to email inquiries.  

PetFinder is updated by volunteers and may not always show current animals in shelter.  For more information and to check availability, please check our website at www.westvalleyhumanesociety.org.  Our website is always up to date.  You can also always reach us on Facebook at @westvalleyhumanesociety.

Our shelter does not adopt animals out of state unless the adopter is willing to travel to the shelter to meet the pet first and arrange transportation.  More details regarding adoption are available on our website.  

"A Pet is a Lifetime Commitment"
